atmAddressTable.name: atmAddressTable
atmAddressTable.description: A table implemented by the network-side of an ATM UNI port, containing the ATM-layer addresses in effect on the user-side of the UNI.

atmAddressEntry.name: atmAddressEntry
atmAddressEntry.description: Information about a single ATM-layer address in effect on the user-side of a UNI port.

axisAtmAddressPort.name: axisAtmAddressPort
axisAtmAddressPort.description: A unique value which identifies this port. The value of 0 has the special meaning of identifying the local UNI.

axisAtmAddressAtmAddress.name: axisAtmAddressAtmAddress
axisAtmAddressAtmAddress.description: The ATM address which is in effect on the user-side of the ATM UNI port.

axisAtmAddressStatus.name: axisAtmAddressStatus
axisAtmAddressStatus.description: An indication of the validity of the ATM address at the user-side of the UNI port.

atmNetPrefixTable.name: atmNetPrefixTable
atmNetPrefixTable.description: A table implemented by the UNI Management Entity on the user-side of an ATM UNI port, containing the network-prefix(es) for ATM-layer addresses in effect on the user-side of the UNI.

atmNetPrefixEntry.name: atmNetPrefixEntry
atmNetPrefixEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the ATM Prefix status.

axisAtmNetPrefixPort.name: axisAtmNetPrefixPort
axisAtmNetPrefixPort.description: The unique value which identifies the ILMI port.

axisAtmNetPrefixPrefix.name: axisAtmNetPrefixPrefix
axisAtmNetPrefixPrefix.description: The network prefix for ATM addresses which is in effect on the user-side of the ATM UNI port.

axisAtmNetPrefixAdminStatus.name: axisAtmNetPrefixAdminStatus
axisAtmNetPrefixAdminStatus.description: An indication of the validity of the network prefix for ATM addresses, on the user-side of the UNI port.

axisAtmNetPrefixOperStatus.name: axisAtmNetPrefixOperStatus
axisAtmNetPrefixOperStatus.description: An indication of the current registration state for the prefix: registering, de-registering, success, fail.

cardLcnPartitionType.name: cardLcnPartitionType
cardLcnPartitionType.description: This object specified the type of partition on LCN: 1. noPartition -- means that all controllers compete for the totoal (G)LCNs limited by the card 2. controllerBased -- means that the total number of (G)LCNs available to each controller is fixed but no reservation on each port. The number for each controller is specified in the smCardResPartGrpTable. 3. portControllerBased -- means that a certain number of (G)LCNs available on each port for each controller is reserved, it is specified in the port resouce partition table. NOTE: This object has to be configured before adding any connections and once a connection is added, this object cannot be changed until all of the connections are deleted.

cardResPartGrpTable.name: cardResPartGrpTable
cardResPartGrpTable.description: This table contains the configuration of all the resource partition(s) that are on the card level, such as (G)LCN (if the object cardLcnPartitionType is configured as controller-based, if not, there is no need to configure this table since it'll be useless).

cardResPartGrpEntry.name: cardResPartGrpEntry
cardResPartGrpEntry.description: This is an entry for a controller

cardResPartCtrlrNum.name: cardResPartCtrlrNum
cardResPartCtrlrNum.description: This object is the index to the table

cardResPartRowStatus.name: cardResPartRowStatus
cardResPartRowStatus.description: This object is records the status of this entry

cardResPartNumOfLcnAvail.name: cardResPartNumOfLcnAvail
cardResPartNumOfLcnAvail.description: This object is configured to reserve the number of (G)LCNs for one controller on a SM card, it can be used on any port but the total number of connections added on all of the ports for that particular controller cannot exceed this number.

diagType.name: diagType
diagType.description: This is used to identify the type of diagnostics. When a trap is sent to report diagnostics results this is used as a varbind to indicate the type of diagnostics.

diagResult.name: diagResult
diagResult.description: This is used to indicate the result of the diagnostics tests in traps.

diagTestId.name: diagTestId
diagTestId.description: This is used to indicate the test number of the diagnostics test that failed.

bertControl.name: bertControl
bertControl.description: This object controls all the SET operations on this MIB group. acquireBert : Acquire BERT resources. cnfBert : Configure the required BERT test. startBert : The configured test has to be started. modBert : Modify parameters for the ongoing BERT test. delBert : Running BERT test has to be stopped. The above list shows the sequence in which the SET operations on this group need to be done, ideally. Bert can be operated upon only with bertUserId and bertSlotNumber. The default value is 0, means no action.

bertResourceStatus.name: bertResourceStatus
bertResourceStatus.description: All of bert resources can be used by only one user at a time. This gives the status of the resources.

bertOwner.name: bertOwner
bertOwner.description: This refers to the user who owns the BERT resources. If the user is a CLI user, then this is username. If it is SV+, then this would be the IP address. For example, this value can be, 192.9.209.157 within quotes.

bertUserId.name: bertUserId
bertUserId.description: This identifies the user who wants to do a SET operation on this group. This will be compared against bertOwner and access will be given only if it matches. Hence, for every SET request, this object should have a valid value. If the user is a CLI user, then this is username. If it is SV+, then this would be the IP address. For example, this value can be, 192.9.209.157 within quotes. Required for bert operations.

bertStatus.name: bertStatus
bertStatus.description: This variable provides the status of BERT in the shelf.

bertSlotNumber.name: bertSlotNumber
bertSlotNumber.description: specifies the physical slot number of the Service Module which is to run BERT For MGX 8220, the range is 5-14. For MGX 8850, the range is 1-6, 9-14, 17-22, 25-30. Required for bert operations.

bertTestMedium.name: bertTestMedium
bertTestMedium.description: specifies whether the bert is to test a port or an entire T1/E1 line. No default value for this, it has to be set if bert is configured.

bertPort.name: bertPort
bertPort.description: specifies the port number for BERT.

bertLine.name: bertLine
bertLine.description: specifies the line number for BERT. If the test medium is port, this represents the line to which the port belongs.

bertMode.name: bertMode
bertMode.description: specifies the mode, the BERT module is to be configured for.

bertDeviceToLoop.name: bertDeviceToLoop
bertDeviceToLoop.description: This shows the type of the end device and the type of the loopback used (latching/nonlatching/polynomial).

bertDS0DPIterationCount.name: bertDS0DPIterationCount
bertDS0DPIterationCount.description: The Iteration Register needs to be programmed in SRM when DSO drop loop option is selected in bertDeviceToLoop. The value to be programmed there is minus one of this object value, since the register is 0 based. DSP-OP devices can be cross connected in the centeral office. By this, the user has capablitiy to put any of the devices in the chain in loopback mode. This is done by repeating the latching activation code in a specific manner. The binary number in the iterataion register determines how many times the first portion of a latching loop activation code needs to be repeated as per user request and according to the Bellcore spec. A value of 0 results in no iteration and will cause the very first device in chain to go into loop back. A value of 1 will result into one iteration and will cause the second device to go into loopback and so on. The range of this count is 1 to 32, and it would translate to a range of 0 to 31 for the iteration register.

bertPattern.name: bertPattern
bertPattern.description: This variable determines BERT pattern to be transmitted.

bertLoopback.name: bertLoopback
bertLoopback.description: specifies the type of loopback to be (d)established.

bertLoopbackOperation.name: bertLoopbackOperation
bertLoopbackOperation.description: specifies the operation of loopback (up or down).

bertDS0Speed.name: bertDS0Speed
bertDS0Speed.description: represents the ds0 speed of the test running.

bertTimeSlots.name: bertTimeSlots
bertTimeSlots.description: represents the number of ds0s in the test medium chosen.

bertStartTime.name: bertStartTime
bertStartTime.description: The syntax is hh:mm:ss The time zone is as configured in the shelf.

bertStartDate.name: bertStartDate
bertStartDate.description: On MGX 8220, the syntax is mm/dd/yy On MGX 8850, the syntax is mm/dd/yyyy

bertBitCount.name: bertBitCount
bertBitCount.description: This shows the number of bits transmitted.

bertBitErrorCount.name: bertBitErrorCount
bertBitErrorCount.description: This shows the number of bits received in error.

bertErrorInjectCount.name: bertErrorInjectCount
bertErrorInjectCount.description: This shows the number of times error was injected.

bertCleanupAction.name: bertCleanupAction
bertCleanupAction.description: When the BERT has to be stopped or aborted (due to card state changes), this object would give the exact action to take. The bert related changes to the shelf, then, can be cleaned up. When its value is a Loopdown, it implies smCleanup plus the corresponding Loopdown.

bertAbortReason.name: bertAbortReason
bertAbortReason.description: when the BERT is aborted, this object would give the reason for that.

bertDDSSeekResultsTableFirstIndex.name: bertDDSSeekResultsTableFirstIndex
bertDDSSeekResultsTableFirstIndex.description: Denotes the index of the oldest entry in the table. A value of zero means that there are no entries in the table.

bertDDSSeekResultsTableLastIndex.name: bertDDSSeekResultsTableLastIndex
bertDDSSeekResultsTableLastIndex.description: Denotes the index of the latest entry in the table. A value of zero means that there are no entries in the table.

bertDDSSeekResultsTable.name: bertDDSSeekResultsTable
bertDDSSeekResultsTable.description: A list of detected DDS codes.

bertDDSSeekResultsTableEntry.name: bertDDSSeekResultsTableEntry
bertDDSSeekResultsTableEntry.description: An entry in the detected DDS codes table.

bertDDSSeekResultsTableIndex.name: bertDDSSeekResultsTableIndex
bertDDSSeekResultsTableIndex.description: Denotes the serial number of the entry in the table.

bertDDSCode.name: bertDDSCode
bertDDSCode.description: Denotes the type of DDS code detected.

bertSupportedTestsTable.name: bertSupportedTestsTable
bertSupportedTestsTable.description: A list of supported tests for a given SM.

bertSupportedTestsTableIndex.name: bertSupportedTestsTableIndex
bertSupportedTestsTableIndex.description: This index is the physical slot number of the Service Module whose entry it represents in the table. For MGX 8220, the range is 5-14. For MGX 8850, the range is 1-6, 9-14, 17-22, 25-30.

bertSupportFlag.name: bertSupportFlag
bertSupportFlag.description: 'yes' if the table entry correctly represents the supported tests for the SM on the corresponding slot. 'no' if no tests at all are supported.

bertTestMediumMask.name: bertTestMediumMask
bertTestMediumMask.description: Every test medium is represented by a bit of mask. Bits 0-1 are valid in this integer. The meaning of the mask can be understood from the example below: -------------------------- TestMedium | SM | support -------------------------- port | 1 line | 1 -------------------------- (Table contents applicable to FRSM-4T1) bertTestMediumMask = 11 binary The column titles represent the variables bertTestMedium depends on. The mask is represented in column major order.

bertModeMask.name: bertModeMask
bertModeMask.description: Every mode is represented by 2 bits of mask. Bits 0-5 are valid in this integer. The meaning of the mask can be understood from the example below: ----------------------------------------------------------- Mode | SM support | Test Medium: | | Multiple | | T1 time slots ----------------------------------------------------------- Pattern test | 1 | 1 DDS seek | 1 | 0 Loopback | 1 | 1 ----------------------------------------------------------- (Table contents applicable to FRSM-4T1) bertModeMask = 101111 binary The column titles represent the variables bertMode depends on. The mask is represented in column major order.

bertDeviceToLoopMask.name: bertDeviceToLoopMask
bertDeviceToLoopMask.description: Every class of devices to loop is represented by 6 bits of mask. Bits 0-29 are valid in this integer. The meaning of the mask can be understood from the example below: ----------------------------------------------------------- | | | Test Medium Class of | SM | MODE |________________________________ devices |supp | Loopback|Line |multiple T1 | 64k | 56k | | | | time slots | | ----------------------------------------------------------- noLatch | 1 0 0 0 0 1 latch | 1 1 0 0 1 1 v54 | 1 1 0 1 1 1 inband/esf| 1 1 1 0 0 0 metallic | 1 0 1 0 0 0 ----------------------------------------------------------- (Table contents applicable to FRSM-4T1) bertDeviceToLoopMask = 001110011000100110000111011111 binary The column titles represent the variables bertDeviceToLoop depends on. The mask is represented in column major order. Due to the limitation on the length of the mask, 'noDevice' option is not represented in this mask. But, the mask for it, is assumed to be a row of ones except for a zero on 'MODE Loopback' column.

bertPatternMask.name: bertPatternMask
bertPatternMask.description: Every class of patterns is represented by 2 bits of mask. Bits 0-3 are valid in this integer. The meaning of the mask can be understood from the example below: ---------------------------------------------- Class of | SM | Non latching patterns | support |device to loop ---------------------------------------------- Other patterns | 1 | 0 ---------------------------------------------- Patterns | 1 | 1 power 9 and 11 | | ---------------------------------------------- (Table contents applicable to FRSM-4T1) bertPatternMask = 1011 binary The column titles represent the variables bertPattern depends on. The mask is represented in column major order.

bertLoopbackMask.name: bertLoopbackMask
bertLoopbackMask.description: Every loopback is represented by 2 bits of mask. Bits 0-5 are valid in this integer. The meaning of the mask can be understood from the example below: ---------------------------------------------- Loopback | SM | Test Medium | support | Port ---------------------------------------------- Far End Loopback | 1 | 1 Facility Loopback | 1 | 1 Metallic Loopback | 1 | 0 ---------------------------------------------- (Table contents applicable to FRSM-4T1) bertLoopbackMask = 011111 binary The column titles represent the variables bertLoopback depends on. The mask is represented in column major order.

bertCardT1E1Type.name: bertCardT1E1Type
bertCardT1E1Type.description: Specifies whether a t1 or e1 card.

srm3T3CnfGrpTable.name: srm3T3CnfGrpTable
srm3T3CnfGrpTable.description: The SRM 3T3 configuration table, it is the distribution of a T3 line.

srm3T3CnfGrpEntry.name: srm3T3CnfGrpEntry
srm3T3CnfGrpEntry.description: an entry in the T3 configuration table

srmT3LineNum.name: srmT3LineNum
srmT3LineNum.description: Select T3 line number. There is no default value for this object.

srmStartT1LineNum.name: srmStartT1LineNum
srmStartT1LineNum.description: The start T1 number to be affected. There is no default value for this object.

srmT1RowStatus.name: srmT1RowStatus
srmT1RowStatus.description: a command is used to add, delete, or modify one or more DS1 mapping. Default value is delete.

srmTargetSlotNum.name: srmTargetSlotNum
srmTargetSlotNum.description: specify the target slot number to be linked. There is no default value for this object. For MGX8850: SRM01 services slots 1 - 6 and 9 - 14, SRM02 services slots 17 - 22 and 25 - 30 For MGX8220: SYNTAX INTEGER (5 ..14)

srmTargetSlotLineNum.name: srmTargetSlotLineNum
srmTargetSlotLineNum.description: 0 means not assigned. There is no default value for this object.

srmeCnfGrpTable.name: srmeCnfGrpTable
srmeCnfGrpTable.description: The SRME configuration table for bulk distribution of SRME lines.

srmeCnfGrpEntry.name: srmeCnfGrpEntry
srmeCnfGrpEntry.description: an entry in the SRME Distribution configuration table

srmeLineNum.name: srmeLineNum
srmeLineNum.description: Select SRME line number. For OC3/STM1: SYNTAX INTEGER 1 There is no default value for this object.

srmeStartVtNum.name: srmeStartVtNum
srmeStartVtNum.description: The start T1 or E1 number (virtual tributary) to be affected. For OC3 with T1 tributaries: SYNTAX INTEGER (1 .. 84) For STM1 with E1 tributaries: SYNTAX INTEGER (1 .. 63) There is no default value for this object.

srmeRowStatus.name: srmeRowStatus
srmeRowStatus.description: Command used to add, delete, or modify one or more T1 or E1 mappings. Only the srmeVtFramingType object can be modified once the distribution link is added. To modify all other objects, user should first delete the link and add it again. Default value is modify.

srmeTargetSlotNum.name: srmeTargetSlotNum
srmeTargetSlotNum.description: specify the target slot number to be linked. There is no default value for this object. For MGX8x50: SRM01 services slots 1 - 6 and 9 - 14, SRM02 services slots 17 - 22 and 25 - 30 For MGX8x30: service slots 3-6 and 10-13

srmeTargetSlotLineNum.name: srmeTargetSlotLineNum
srmeTargetSlotLineNum.description: Specify the target slot's line to be linked. 0 means not assigned. There is no default value for this object.

srmeVtFramingType.name: srmeVtFramingType
srmeVtFramingType.description: Specifies the Framing Type of the target slot line. This is applicable only if the target module is a T1 Service Module and byte sync mapping is used on SRME. Not applicable to E1 Service Modules. sf: Superframe or D4 esf: Extended Superframe. Default is esf if SRME lines are configured for byte-synchronous mapping. Else, the default is notApplicable.

serialPortNumOfValidEntries.name: serialPortNumOfValidEntries
serialPortNumOfValidEntries.description: Number of rows in serialPortTable. This number is equal to the number of serial ports on the module.

serialInterfaceTable.name: serialInterfaceTable
serialInterfaceTable.description: This table represents Physical serial interfaces on the module

serialInterfaceEntry.name: serialInterfaceEntry
serialInterfaceEntry.description: An entry for the serial interface

serialPortNum.name: serialPortNum
serialPortNum.description: serial interface number port 1. is always defined as debug port port 2. on BSC can perform SLIP.

serialPortType.name: serialPortType
serialPortType.description: On the BSC board IP stack is mounted on the manager port, on the debug port dumb terminal can be connected function of the ports cannot be changed, except for enabling and disabling

serialPortEnable.name: serialPortEnable
serialPortEnable.description: ports can be enabled or diabled

serialPortbps.name: serialPortbps
serialPortbps.description: baud rate of the ports, each port can be config different

ethernetPhysicaAddress.name: ethernetPhysicaAddress
ethernetPhysicaAddress.description: ethernet address stored in the BSC BRAM, entered by manfacturing.

asmAlarmTable.name: asmAlarmTable
asmAlarmTable.description: The ASM Alarm table. The table size is given by the value of ASMNumOfValidEntries.

asmAlarmEntry.name: asmAlarmEntry
asmAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the Basis ASM Alarm Table.

asmAlarmNum.name: asmAlarmNum
asmAlarmNum.description: This object is the identifier of a ASM alarm entry. The Alarm is further identified by the objects ASMAlarmType & ASMAlarmUnitNum.

asmAlarmType.name: asmAlarmType
asmAlarmType.description: The value for this object indicates the type of Alarm represented in the entry of ASMAlarmTable indexed by ASMAlarmNum.

asmAlarmUnitNum.name: asmAlarmUnitNum
asmAlarmUnitNum.description: This object identifies one unit among a number of identical units represented in ASMAlarmTable having the same ASMAlarmType.

asmAlarmThreshold.name: asmAlarmThreshold
asmAlarmThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold beyond which the alarmable unit is said to be in an abnormal state.

asmAlarmSeverity.name: asmAlarmSeverity
asmAlarmSeverity.description: This variable specifies the severity of the alarm to be declared when the ASMAlarmThreshold specified is exceeded for the entry of ASMAlarmTable indexed by ASMAlarmNum.

asmUnitMeasurable.name: asmUnitMeasurable
asmUnitMeasurable.description: This object indicates if the alarm unit is measurable by the AXIS shelf.

asmUnitMeasuredValue.name: asmUnitMeasuredValue
asmUnitMeasuredValue.description: This object gives the mesaured value of the entity addressed by asmAlarmNum if it is measurable.

asmPhysicalAlarmState.name: asmPhysicalAlarmState
asmPhysicalAlarmState.description: This object indicates the status of the ASM alarm represented in this entry. It is a bitmap where a set bit indicates an abnormal condition. A reset bit signifies normal operation.

asmClrButton.name: asmClrButton
asmClrButton.description: This object when set to ASMAlarmClear causes the entry in the ASMAlarmTable represented by ASMAlarmNum to be cleared.

asmNumOfValidEntries.name: asmNumOfValidEntries
asmNumOfValidEntries.description: The number of valid ASMAlarmTable entries (regardless of how many are actually configured) in the table.

asmShelfAlarmState.name: asmShelfAlarmState
asmShelfAlarmState.description: This object indicates whether any Shelf Alarm has been declared in the BASIS system.

primaryMuxClockSource.name: primaryMuxClockSource
primaryMuxClockSource.description: Primary Mux Clock source for AUM card.

secondaryMuxClockSource.name: secondaryMuxClockSource
secondaryMuxClockSource.description: Secondary clock source for AUM card.

currentClock.name: currentClock
currentClock.description: clock source currently selected for AUM card.

extClockPresent.name: extClockPresent
extClockPresent.description: Status of External T1/E1 Clock on AUM card.

extClkSrcImpedance.name: extClkSrcImpedance
extClkSrcImpedance.description: Impedance on external clock input for AUM card.

extClkConnectorType.name: extClkConnectorType
extClkConnectorType.description: This object describes the type of connector available for connecting the external clock source to the AUM-LM. The T3 and E3 cards are separate hence this field is not configurable for any BNM card type except bnm-155

aumAddressTranslationTable.name: aumAddressTranslationTable
aumAddressTranslationTable.description: This table contains address translation parameters for AXIS connections.

aumAddressTranslationEntry.name: aumAddressTranslationEntry
aumAddressTranslationEntry.description: This entry exists when the connection specified by connShelfNum, connSlotNum and connChanNum exists.

connShelfNum.name: connShelfNum
connShelfNum.description: Index to shelf list on BASIS.

connSlotNum.name: connSlotNum
connSlotNum.description: Index to slot list on BASIS.

connChanNum.name: connChanNum
connChanNum.description: Index to channel list on BASIS.

aumConnType.name: aumConnType
aumConnType.description: Virtual channel connection or Virtual Path Connection

connVPINum.name: connVPINum
connVPINum.description: Virtual channel connection or Virtual Path Connection

aumAddressTranslationDeleteTable.name: aumAddressTranslationDeleteTable
aumAddressTranslationDeleteTable.description: This table contains address translation parameters for AXIS connections.

aumAddressTranslationDeleteEntry.name: aumAddressTranslationDeleteEntry
aumAddressTranslationDeleteEntry.description: This entry controls bulk deletion of connections on a given AXIS slot.

delShelfNum.name: delShelfNum
delShelfNum.description: Index to shelf list on AXIS.

delSlotNum.name: delSlotNum
delSlotNum.description: Index to slot list on BASIS.

bnmPortCounterTable.name: bnmPortCounterTable
bnmPortCounterTable.description: The counter table is for the ATM interface, initially there is only one interface, but by making it a table multiple ATM interfaces can be accommodated later.

bnmPortCounterEntry.name: bnmPortCounterEntry
bnmPortCounterEntry.description: An entry for DS3 ATM counters

bnmPortCounterIndex.name: bnmPortCounterIndex
bnmPortCounterIndex.description: This specifies the BNM port being referenced.

bnmPortRcvCells.name: bnmPortRcvCells
bnmPortRcvCells.description: The count of Received cells at the BNM port.

bnmPortXmtCells.name: bnmPortXmtCells
bnmPortXmtCells.description: The count of cells transmitted by the BNM port.

bnmPortCounterClrButton.name: bnmPortCounterClrButton
bnmPortCounterClrButton.description: This object when set to bnmPortCounterClear causes all counters in the row referenced by bnmPortCounterIndex to be cleared.

bnmPortRcvCellRate.name: bnmPortRcvCellRate
bnmPortRcvCellRate.description: The number of cells received from the BNM port (trunk) per second .

bnmPortRcvUtilization.name: bnmPortRcvUtilization
bnmPortRcvUtilization.description: The received percentage utilization of the BNM port (trunk)

bnmPortXmtCellRate.name: bnmPortXmtCellRate
bnmPortXmtCellRate.description: The number of cells transmitted to the BNM port (trunk) per second.

bnmPortXmtUtilization.name: bnmPortXmtUtilization
bnmPortXmtUtilization.description: The transmitted percentage utilization of the BNM port (trunk)

bnmPortCounterNumOfValidEntries.name: bnmPortCounterNumOfValidEntries
bnmPortCounterNumOfValidEntries.description: This object specifies the number of rows in bnmPortCounterTable.

bnmCellbusXmtCellCount.name: bnmCellbusXmtCellCount
bnmCellbusXmtCellCount.description: This objects is a count of cells transmitted by the BNM Cell Bus Master to the cell bus.

bnmCellbusNoAckCellCount.name: bnmCellbusNoAckCellCount
bnmCellbusNoAckCellCount.description: This object is a count of cells transmitted by the BNM Cell Bus Master to the cell bus for which no acknowledgement was received i.e the slave card was missing or inactive.

bnmCellbusGrantCount.name: bnmCellbusGrantCount
bnmCellbusGrantCount.description: This object is a count of receiver grants given by the BNM Cell Bus Master

bnmEgressXmtCellCountDuringAlarm.name: bnmEgressXmtCellCountDuringAlarm
bnmEgressXmtCellCountDuringAlarm.description: This object is a count of cells transmitted by the Egress Engine to the port i while a T3 Alarm condition was in effect.

bnmEgressInvalidCellCount.name: bnmEgressInvalidCellCount
bnmEgressInvalidCellCount.description: This object is a count of cells with disabled channel headers, received by the Egress Engine on the BNM and dropped.

bnmEgressInvalidCellHdr.name: bnmEgressInvalidCellHdr
bnmEgressInvalidCellHdr.description: This object gives the header of the first invalid cell that was dropped by the Egress Engine on the BNM since this object was last read and/or cleared.

bnmIngressInvalidCellCount.name: bnmIngressInvalidCellCount
bnmIngressInvalidCellCount.description: This object is a count of cells from disabled channels received by the Ingress Engine on the BNM. This is not available in Release 1.

bnmIngressInvalidCellHdr.name: bnmIngressInvalidCellHdr
bnmIngressInvalidCellHdr.description: This object gives the header of the first invalid cell that was dropped by the Ingress Engine on the BNM since this object was last read and/or cleared. This is not available in Release 1.

bnmCountersClrButton.name: bnmCountersClrButton
bnmCountersClrButton.description: This object clears the BNM counters

bnmLineInterfaceFormat.name: bnmLineInterfaceFormat
bnmLineInterfaceFormat.description: This indicates the format of the cells going out on the BNM trunk For T3 and E3 cards its currently fixed at STI mode. BNM-155 sonet cards can take on UNI or NNI options

pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource.name: pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource
pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource.description: Primary Mux Clock source for PXM card. For pxmInbandClock1 and pxmInbandClock2, the pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber described the Line number that the clock is derived from. For pxmServiceModuleClock1 and pxmServiceModuleClock2, the pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber described the SM slot number For pxmExternalClock and pxmExternalClock2, pxmPrimaryExternalClockSourcePortNumber describes the Port number from where the clock is derived. Also the pxmExtClockPresent and pxmExtClkConnectorType are used with the pxmExternalClock. And pxmExtClock2Present and pxmExtClk2ConnectorType are used with pxmExternalClock2.

pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.name: pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber
pxmPrimaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.description: If pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource is pxmInbandClock1 (1) or pxmServiceModuleClock2 (5), then this entry indicates Inband Line number.

pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.name: pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber
pxmPrimarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.description: If pxmPrimaryMuxClockSource is pxmServiceModuleClock1(2) or pxmServiceModuleClock2 (6), then this entry indicates SM slot number.

pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource.name: pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource
pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource.description: Secondary clock source for PXM card. For pxmInbandClock1 and pxmInbandClock2, the pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber described the Line number that the clock is derived from. For pxmServiceModuleClock1 and pxmServiceModuleClock2, the pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber described the SM slot number pxmSecondaryExternalClockSourcePortNumber describes the Port number from where the clock is derived. Also the pxmExtClockPresent and pxmExtClkConnectorType are used with the pxmExternalClock. And pxmExtClockPresent2 and pxmExtClkConnectorType2 are used with pxmExternalClock2.

pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.name: pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber
pxmSecondaryInbandClockSourceLineNumber.description: If pxmSecondaryMuxClockSource is pxmInbandClock1 (1) or pxmServiceModuleClock2 (5), then this entry indicates Inband Line number .

pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber.name: pxmSecondarySMClockSourceSlotNumber

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndexNext.description: This object contains an appropriate value to be used for pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex when creating entries in the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable. The value 0 indicates that no unassigned entries are available. To obtain the pxmAtmVpCrossConnectIndex value for a new entry, the manager issues a management protocol retrieval operation to obtain the current value of this object. After each retrieval, the agent should modify the value to the next unassigned index.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable.description: The ATM VC Cross Connect table. A bi- directional VC cross-connect which cross-connects two end points (i.e., VCLs) is modeled as one entry in this table.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntry
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.description: An entry in the ATM VC Cross Connect table. This entry is used to model a bi-directional ATM VC cross-connect cross-connecting two end points. Step-wise Procedures to set up a VC Cross-connect Once the entries in the pxmAtmVclTable are created, the following procedures are used to cross-connect the VCLs together to form a VCC segment. (1) The manager obtains a unique pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex by reading the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndexNext object. (2) Next, the manager creates a set of one or more rows in the ATM VC Cross Connect Table, one for each cross-connection between two VCLs. Each row is indexed by the ATM interface port numbers and VPI/VCI values of the two ends of that cross-connection. This set of rows specifies the topology of the VCC cross-connect and is identified by a single value of pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex. Negotiated VC Cross-Connect Establishment (2a) The manager creates a row in this table by setting pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus to createAndWait(5). The agent checks the requested topology and the mutual sanity of the ATM traffic parameters and QoS Classes, i.e., the row creation fails if: - the requested topology is not supported by the agent, - the traffic/QoS parameter values associated with the requested row are incompatible with those of already existing rows for this VC cross-connect. [For example, for setting up a point-to-point VC cross-connect, the ATM traffic parameters in the receive direction of a VCL at the low end of the cross-connect must equal to the traffic parameters in the transmit direction of the other VCL at the high end of the cross-connect, otherwise, the row creation fails.] The agent also checks for internal errors in building the cross-connect. The pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex values in the corresponding pxmAtmVclTable rows are filled in by the agent at this point. (2b) The manager promotes the row in the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable by setting pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus to active(1). If this set is successful, the agent has reserved the resources specified by the ATM traffic parameter and QoS Class values for each direction of the VC cross-connect in an ATM switch or network. (3) The manager sets the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus to up(1) in all rows of this VC cross-connect to turn the traffic flow on. One-Shot VC Cross-Connect Establishment A VC cross-connect may also be established in one step by a set-request with all necessary parameter values and pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus set to createAndGo(4). In contrast to the negotiated VC cross-connect establishment which allows for detailed error checking i.e., set errors are explicitly linked to particular resource acquisition failures), the one-shot VC cross-connect establishment performs the setup on one operation but does not have the advantage of step-wise error checking. VC Cross-Connect Retirement A VC cross-connect identified by a particular value of pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex is released by: (1) Setting pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus of all rows identified by this value of pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex to destroy(6). The agent may release all associated resources, and the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex values in the corresponding pxmAtmVclTable row are removed. Note that a situation when only a subset of the associated rows are deleted corresponds to a VC topology change. (2) After deletion of the appropriate pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntries, the manager may set pxmAtmVclRowStatus to destroy(6) the associated VCLs. The agent releases the resources and removes the associated rows in the pxmAtmVclTable. VC Cross-Connect Reconfiguration At the discretion of the agent, a VC cross-connect may be reconfigured by adding and/or deleting leafs to/from the VC topology as per the VC cross-connect establishment/retirement procedures. Reconfiguration of traffic/QoS parameter values requires release of the VC cross-connect before those parameter values may by changed for individual VCLs.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectIndex.description: A unique value to identify this VC cross-connect.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value of the ATM interface port for this VC cross-connect. The term low implies that this ATM interface has the numerically lower ifIndex value than the other ATM interface identified in the same pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVpi.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVpi
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVpi.description: The value of this object is equal to the VPI value at the ATM interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex. The VPI value cannot exceed the number supported by the pxmAtmInterfaceMaxVpiBits at the low ATM interface port.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVci.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVci
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowVci.description: The value of this object is equal to the VCI value at the ATM interface associated with this VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex. The VCI value cannot exceed the number supported by the pxmAtmInterfaceMaxVciBits at the low ATM interface port.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex.description: The value of this object is equal to MIB II's ifIndex value for the ATM interface port for this VC cross-connect. The term high implies that this VC cross-connect that this ATM interface has the numerically higher ifIndex value than the other ATM interface identified in the same pxmAtmVcCrossConnectEntry.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVpi.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVpi
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVpi.description: The value of this object is equal to the VPI value at the ATM interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex. The VPI value cannot exceed the number supported by the pxmAtmInterfaceMaxVpiBits at the high ATM interface port.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVci.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVci
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighVci.description: The value of this object is equal to the VCI value at the ATM interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex. The VCI value cannot exceed the number supported by the pxmAtmInterfaceMaxVciBits at the high ATM interface port.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the desired administrative status of this bi-directional VC cross-connect. The up and down states indicate that the traffic flow is enabled or disabled respectively on this VC cross-connect.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HOperStatus.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HOperStatus
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HOperStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the current operational status of the VC cross-connect in one direction; (i.e., from the low to high direction). The up and down states indicate that this ATM VC cross-connect from low to high direction is operational or not operational respectively. The unknown state indicates that the state of it cannot be determined.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LOperStatus.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LOperStatus
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LOperStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the current operational status of the VC cross-connect in one direction; (i.e., from the high to low direction). The up and down states indicate that this ATM VC cross-connect from high to low direction is operational or not operational respectively. The unknown state indicates that the state of it cannot be determined.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HLastChange.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HLastChange
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectL2HLastChange.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the time this VC cross-connect entered its current operational state in low to high direction. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LLastChange.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LLastChange
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectH2LLastChange.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the time this VC cross-connect entered its current operational state in high to low direction. If the current state was entered prior to the last re-initialization of the agent, then this object contains a zero value.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectRowStatus.description: The status of this entry in the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectTable. This object is used to create a new cross-connect for cross-connecting VCLs which are created using the pxmAtmVclTable or to change or delete existing cross-connect. This object must be initially set to `createAndWait' or `createAndGo'. This object cannot be set to `active' unless the following columnar object exists in this row: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus. To turn on a VC cross-connect, the pxmAtmVcCrossConnectAdminStatus is set to `up'.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighAddressType.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighAddressType
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighAddressType.description: The value of this object identifies the address type of the interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectHighIfIndex. If the address type is pxmAtmUni, the first 4 bits of the VPI field is the GFCI and the remaing 12 bits of the VPI field is the VPI. If the address type is pxmAtmNni, the whole 16 bits of the VPI is the VPI. If the address type is the frameRelay, the combination of the VPI field and the VCI field are the DLCI.

pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowAddressType.name: pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowAddressType
pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowAddressType.description: The value of this object identifies the address type of the interface associated with the VC cross-connect that is identified by pxmAtmVcCrossConnectLowIfIndex. If the address type is pxmAtmUni, the first 4 bits of the VPI field is the GFCI and the remaing 12 bits of the VPI field is the VPI. If the address type is pxmAtmNni, the whole 16 bits of the VPI is the VPI. If the address type is the frameRelay, the combination of the VPI field and the VCI field are the DLCI.

bbIfRscPrtEgrPctBandwidth.name: bbIfRscPrtEgrPctBandwidth

bbIfStateGrpEntry.description: An entry for logical interface. In MGX PXM card, a physical port can have a maximum of 32 logical interfaces.

bbStateIfNum.name: bbStateIfNum
bbStateIfNum.description: This is logical interface number within a physical line num. In MGX PXM card, a physical port can have a maximum of 32 logical interfaces.

bbIfState.description: This variable indicates the status of the logical interface. The following are not supported for the logical interface. -- remoteloopback (3), -- outofcelldelineation (6), -- localloopback (7)

bbIfOversubscribed.description: This variable indicates the whether the logical interface is over subscribed or not.

bbChanCnfGrpEntry.description: The config table is for logical channel.

bbChanCnfNum.name: bbChanCnfNum
bbChanCnfNum.description: This identifies a channel on the PXM logical interface, used as PXM port.

bbChanRowStatus.name: bbChanRowStatus
bbChanRowStatus.description: This will add, delete or modify the channel 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY

bbChanConnType.name: bbChanConnType
bbChanConnType.description: This specifies the connection type 1 ==> Virtual Path Connection 2 ==> Virtual Channel Connection

bbChanServiceType.name: bbChanServiceType
bbChanServiceType.description: This specifies the service type 1 ==> Constant Bit Rate 2 ==> Variable Bit Rate 3 ==> Available Bit Rate 4 ==> Unspecified Bit Rate 5 ==> Variable Bit Rate - Real Time

bbChanConnDesc.name: bbChanConnDesc
bbChanConnDesc.description: A string that has been defined to give a descriptive name to the connection

bbChanSvcFlag.name: bbChanSvcFlag
bbChanSvcFlag.description: This specifies the connection type 1 ==> SVC connection 2 ==> PVC connection, used by PAR 3 ==> Soft PVC connection, used by PNNI

bbChanSvcConnId.name: bbChanSvcConnId
bbChanSvcConnId.description: This connection ID is for future use Currently not supported.

bbChanIfNum.name: bbChanIfNum
bbChanIfNum.description: Channel's logical Interface from which traffic of the connection will be received.

bbChanUpcPCR.name: bbChanUpcPCR
bbChanUpcPCR.description: PCR(0+1), Peak Cell Rate, specifies an upper bound on rate at which traffic can be submitted on an ATM connection. This object applies to the First Leaky Bucket for leaving cells with Cell Loss Priority of 0 or 1. . Units: cells per second. . Applicable connection types: UBR, CBR, VBR, ABR . Default: 50 . Ranges: T3 : 50-96000 E3 : 50-80000 OC3 : 50-353208 OC12: 50-1412832

bbChanUpcCDVT.name: bbChanUpcCDVT
bbChanUpcCDVT.description: Compliant Cell Delay Variation. Also known as CDVT(0+1), Cell Delay Variation Tolerance, which specifies the maximum time period for accumulated violations of cell-arrival time parameters. This object applies to the First Leaky bucket for cells with Cell Loss Priority of 0 or 1. . Units: microseconds. . Applicable connection types: UBR, CBR, VBR, ABR . Default: CBR: 10000 Others: 250000

bbChanUpcSCR.name: bbChanUpcSCR
bbChanUpcSCR.description: SCR, Sustainable Cell Rate, is an upper bound on the conforming average rate of an ATM connection, over time scales which are long relative to those for which the PCR is defined. Enforcement of this bound by the UPC could allow the network to allocate sufficient resources, but less than thos based on the PCR, and still ensure that the performance objectives (e.g., Cell Loss Ratio) can be achieved. . Units: cell per second. . Applicable connection types: . VBR, ABR . Ranges: T3 : 50-96000 E3 : 50-80000 OC3 : 50-353208 OC12: 50-1412832 . Default: 50

bbChanUpcMBS.name: bbChanUpcMBS
bbChanUpcMBS.description: Maximum Burst Size (MBS). Also known as Compliant Burst Size (CBS). . Units: cells . Applicable connection types: . VBR, ABR . Default: 1000 . Range : 1-5000000

bbChanGcra1Action.name: bbChanGcra1Action
bbChanGcra1Action.description: GCRA1 Action. 1 = No Action 2 = Tag Untagged cells 3 = Tag untagged cells and discard tagged cells 4 = Discard all (0+1) non-comforming cells

bbChanGcra2Action.name: bbChanGcra2Action
bbChanGcra2Action.description: GCRA2 Action. 1 = No Action 2 = Tag Untagged cells 3 = Tag untagged cells and discard tagged cells 4 = Discard all (0+1) non-comforming cells

bbChanUpcSCRPolicing.name: bbChanUpcSCRPolicing
bbChanUpcSCRPolicing.description: Selects SCR policing for CLP = 0 or all cells

bbChanEfciThreshold.name: bbChanEfciThreshold
bbChanEfciThreshold.description: Threshold above which EFCI bit is to be set. Default Value is 3/4 of max cell count.

bbChanDiscardOption.name: bbChanDiscardOption
bbChanDiscardOption.description: Enable Frame Discard or CLP Hysteresis.

bbChanFrmDiscardThreshold.name: bbChanFrmDiscardThreshold
bbChanFrmDiscardThreshold.description: Ingress Frame Discard Threshold. Valid only when Ingress Frame Discard option is selected. Default Value : TBD

bbChanClpHiThreshold.name: bbChanClpHiThreshold
bbChanClpHiThreshold.description: Ingress CLP High Threshold. Default is 3/4 of max cell count.

bbChanClpLoThreshold.name: bbChanClpLoThreshold
bbChanClpLoThreshold.description: Ingress CLP Low Threshold. Valid only when Ingress CLP Hysteresis option is selected. Default Value is 1/2 of max cell count.

bbChanCongstUpdateCode.name: bbChanCongstUpdateCode
bbChanCongstUpdateCode.description: Ingress Channel Congestion Update Code. Default Value : TBD

bbChanMaxCellMemThreshold.name: bbChanMaxCellMemThreshold
bbChanMaxCellMemThreshold.description: Maximum number of cells of that connection in the memory. Assuming Total Cell Memory is 512K cells, this is defaulted to half of total size.

bbChanIngrPercentUtil.name: bbChanIngrPercentUtil
bbChanIngrPercentUtil.description: Percentage Utilization of the IngrService Rate. This is used for connection admission control. Default Value : TBD

bbChanEgrPercentUtil.name: bbChanEgrPercentUtil
bbChanEgrPercentUtil.description: Percentage Utilization of the EgrService Rate. This is used for egress bandwidth calculation and connection admission control. Default Value : TBD

bbChanEgrSrvRate.name: bbChanEgrSrvRate
bbChanEgrSrvRate.description: Egress service rate - This is used for egress bandwidth calculation and for connection admission control. The actual value depends on the speed of the logical interface

bbChanOvrSubOvrRide.name: bbChanOvrSubOvrRide
bbChanOvrSubOvrRide.description: Channel Over Subscrive Override This MIB variable allows one to add a new connection on a port even if it is over subscribed.

bbChanLocalVpi.name: bbChanLocalVpi
bbChanLocalVpi.description: The VPI value for this channel

bbChanLocalVci.name: bbChanLocalVci
bbChanLocalVci.description: The VCI value for this channel

bbChanLocalNsapAddr.name: bbChanLocalNsapAddr
bbChanLocalNsapAddr.description: The Near End NSAP Address value for this channel.

bbChanRemoteVpi.name: bbChanRemoteVpi
bbChanRemoteVpi.description: The VPI value for this channel

bbChanRemoteVci.name: bbChanRemoteVci
bbChanRemoteVci.description: The VCI value for this channel

bbChanRemoteNsapAddr.name: bbChanRemoteNsapAddr
bbChanRemoteNsapAddr.description: The Far End NSAP Address value for this channel.

bbChanMaster.name: bbChanMaster
bbChanMaster.description: This is used by the PXM switch platform module, to determine if this endpoint ia master or slave.

bbChanRtePriority.name: bbChanRtePriority
bbChanRtePriority.description: This is also known as class of service, it is used by PXM to determine how important this connection is when selecting connections to route.

bbChanMaxCost.name: bbChanMaxCost
bbChanMaxCost.description: Maximum allowed cost. It is related to Cost Based Routing. This is used by PXM so that it won't choose a path with a cost greater than this configured level.

bbChanRestrictTrkType.name: bbChanRestrictTrkType
bbChanRestrictTrkType.description: Restricted trunk type for routind, used by PXM. It specifies that the connection either cannot be routed over satellite trunks or terrestrial trunks, or it can be on any type of trunk.

bbChanTestType.name: bbChanTestType
bbChanTestType.description: The chanTestType starts testing the continuity or delay of a connection. It sends specific cell patterns toward the network and the terminating end of this connection has to be an AXIS or ASI of a BPX in order for this test to be working. The receiving node would loop back when it receives these cells. The test should be done in about couple of seconds. The testcon tests the continuity of the connection and testdelay uses the same test except that it measures for delay through the network. To test the delay follow this procedure: a- set chanTestType to testdelay b- read chanTestState till it is Pass or Fail c- Read chanTestResult for the delay if it is Pass *Note that the chanTestType would go back to notest when the test is completed To test the continuity follow this procedure: a- set chanTestType to testcon b- read chanTestState till it is Pass or Fail *Note that the chanTestType would go back to notest when the test is completed You CAN NOT select 2 tests back to back, you have selcelt one and wait the result and then start the other one. SYNTAX When you select testdelay This is the type of the test 1 = Test Continuity 2 = Test Delay 3 = No Test tstconseg is performed on the port side, i.e, towards the CPE

bbChanTestState.name: bbChanTestState
bbChanTestState.description: This shows the state of the test When you add a connection then the chanTestState becomes notinprogress and when you select any test, it would go to inprogress state and after it completes the test, it will go to failed or passed state. 1 = Passed 2 = Failed 3 = In Progress 4 = Not In Progress

bbChanTestResult.name: bbChanTestResult
bbChanTestResult.description: This is round trip delay in milliseconds. When you select testdelay option for the chanTestType, the result of the test that is measured in milliseconds can be read in chanTestResult.

bbChanTestTypeCPESide.name: bbChanTestTypeCPESide
bbChanTestTypeCPESide.description: The default is notest. The chanTestType starts testing the segment continuity of a connection. It sends OAM Segment loopback cell towards port side (CPE) The CPE would loop back the cell To test the continuity follow this procedure: a- set chanTestTypeCPEside to testconseg b- read chanTestState till it is Pass or Fail *Note that the chanTestType would go back to notest when the test is completed SYNTAX When you select testdelay This is the type of the test 1 = Test Continuity 2 = No Test

bbChanTestStateCPESide.name: bbChanTestStateCPESide
bbChanTestStateCPESide.description: This shows the state of the test When you add a connection then the chanTestState becomes notinprogress and when you select any test, it would go to inprogress state and after it completes the test, it will go to failed or passed state. 1 = Passed 2 = Failed 3 = In Progress 4 = Not In Progress

bbConnVpcFlag.name: bbConnVpcFlag
bbConnVpcFlag.description: This represents the connection type, used for PXM to identify VPC/VCC

bbConnServiceType.name: bbConnServiceType
bbConnServiceType.description: This specifies the service type 1 ==> Constant Bit Rate 2 ==> Variable Bit Rate 4 ==> Unspecified Bit Rate 6 ==> Available Bit Rate ( standard ) 8 ==> Variable Bit Rate - Real-Time Note that this is used by PXM card, Also to make it compatible with existing AUSM MIB definition, value 3 is not used. foresight ABR is not supported in PXM , i.e Virtual Service Module

bbConnPCR.name: bbConnPCR
bbConnPCR.description: Peak cell rate, could be derived from the end point parameter

bbConnSCR.name: bbConnSCR
bbConnSCR.description: Sustained cell rate, could be derived from the end point parameter

bbConnPercentUtil.name: bbConnPercentUtil
bbConnPercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by this end-point.

bbRemoteConnPCR.name: bbRemoteConnPCR
bbRemoteConnPCR.description: Peak cell rate of the other end, if not set, will be set to the same as local end PCR (bbChanUpcPCR). However, note that if the PCRs for both local and remote end are set to the different value (i.e., asymmetric conn), then this should be set differently from local end PCR.

bbRemoteConnSCR.name: bbRemoteConnSCR
bbRemoteConnSCR.description: Sustained cell rate of the other end, if not set, will be set to the same as local end SCR (bbChanUpcSCR). However, note that if the PCRs for both local and remote end are set to the different value (i.e., asymmetric conn), then this should be set differently from local end SCR.

bbRemoteConnPercentUtil.name: bbRemoteConnPercentUtil
bbRemoteConnPercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by this end-point. If this is not specified in the connection setup request, it'll be defaulted to 100 percent

bbChanUpcMCR.name: bbChanUpcMCR
bbChanUpcMCR.description: SCR, Sustainable Cell Rate, is an upper bound on the conforming average rate of an ATM connection, over time scales which are long relative to those for which the PCR is defined. Enforcement of this bound by the UPC could allow the network to allocate sufficient resources, but less than thos based on the PCR, and still ensure that the performance objectives (e.g., Cell Loss Ratio) can be achieved. . Units: cell per second. . Applicable connection types: . ABR . Ranges: T3 : 50-96000 E3 : 50-80000 OC3 : 50-353208 OC12: 50-1412832 . Default: 50

bbChanNumNextAvailable.name: bbChanNumNextAvailable
bbChanNumNextAvailable.description: This variable contains the next unused channel number of the possible 4096 . This number can be used in channel config table. ChanNumNextAvailable gets updated whenever this number is used to create a new logical channel. Value 0 for this variable indicates that no more channels are available.

bbChanVpIdNextAvailable.name: bbChanVpIdNextAvailable
bbChanVpIdNextAvailable.description: This in only valid for a Service Module, will NOT be used in PXM. This variable contains the next unused local VPId of the possible 1 to 4095. This number can be used in channel config table. It gets updated if the number is used to create a new vp connection. The max. no. of VP conn.s is limited to the VPI range configured for this logical interface. Value of 0 for this variable indicates that no more vp connections are available

bbChanCntGrpTable.name: bbChanCntGrpTable
bbChanCntGrpTable.description: The Broadband Channel count table is for a channel on virtual interface or a physical line. There will an entry for each of the channel added on the logical partition of the physical line.

bbChanCntGrpEntry.name: bbChanCntGrpEntry
bbChanCntGrpEntry.description: The count table is for logical channel. The available number of channels on the broadband interface on the PXM card is restricted to 4K. The PXM card has 2 Queue Engines ( QE0 and QE1).

bbChanRcvClp0Cells.name: bbChanRcvClp0Cells
bbChanRcvClp0Cells.description: CLP_0 Cells Received From Port Count.

bbChanRcvClp1Cells.name: bbChanRcvClp1Cells
bbChanRcvClp1Cells.description: CLP_1 Cells Received From Port Count.

bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra1Policer.name: bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra1Policer
bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra1Policer.description: Non-Conforming Cells Received at Ingress GCRA1 Policer Count.

bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra2Policer.name: bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra2Policer
bbChanNonConformCellsAtGcra2Policer.description: Non-Conforming Cells Received at Ingress GCRA2 Policer Count.

bbChanRcvEOFCells.name: bbChanRcvEOFCells
bbChanRcvEOFCells.description: Number of cells received from PXM port with EOF set.

bbChanDscdClp0Cells.name: bbChanDscdClp0Cells
bbChanDscdClp0Cells.description: Number of discarded clp = 0 cells received from PXM port.

bbChanDscdClp1Cells.name: bbChanDscdClp1Cells
bbChanDscdClp1Cells.description: Number of discarded clp = 1 cells received from PXM port.

bbChanRcvCellsSent.name: bbChanRcvCellsSent
bbChanRcvCellsSent.description: Number of cells received from port and sent out of the Queue Engine.

bbChanXmtClp0Cells.name: bbChanXmtClp0Cells
bbChanXmtClp0Cells.description: Number of cells with EFCI clear transmitted to PXM port.

bbChanXmtClp1Cells.name: bbChanXmtClp1Cells
bbChanXmtClp1Cells.description: Number of cells with EFCI set transmitted to PXM port.

bbChanDscdClpZeroCellsToPort.name: bbChanDscdClpZeroCellsToPort
bbChanDscdClpZeroCellsToPort.description: Number of discard CLP = 0 cells before transmitted to PXM port.

bbChanDscdClpOneCellsToPort.name: bbChanDscdClpOneCellsToPort
bbChanDscdClpOneCellsToPort.description: Number of discard CLP = 1 cells before transmitted to PXM port.

bbChanCntClrButton.name: bbChanCntClrButton
bbChanCntClrButton.description: Writing a value of 2 resets all the counters

bbChanStateGrpTable.name: bbChanStateGrpTable
bbChanStateGrpTable.description: The Broadband Channel state table is for a channel on logical interface. There will an entry for each of the channel added on the logical partition of the physical line.

bbChanStateGrpEntry.name: bbChanStateGrpEntry
bbChanStateGrpEntry.description: The state table is for logical channel. The available number of channels on the broadband interface (user ports) on the PXM card is restricted to 4K. The PXM card has 2 Queue Engines ( QE0 and QE1). Current calculations allow 31954 GLCNs on QE0, and 31748 GLCNs on QE1.

bbChanStateNum.name: bbChanStateNum
bbChanStateNum.description: Refers to the logical channel number

bbChanState.name: bbChanState
bbChanState.description: This variable indicates the state of the VC (channel).

bbChanEgrXmtState.name: bbChanEgrXmtState
bbChanEgrXmtState.description: Indicates the status of port transmit(Egress)

bbChanIngrRcvState.name: bbChanIngrRcvState
bbChanIngrRcvState.description: indicates the status of port receive(Ingress)

vrtlIntrConfigEntry.name: vrtlIntrConfigEntry
vrtlIntrConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Virtual Interface configuration Table

configVrtlIntrNum.name: configVrtlIntrNum
configVrtlIntrNum.description: Virtual Interface Number. There are totaly 32 Virtual Interfaces on the card (egress).

vrtlIntrPortNum.name: vrtlIntrPortNum
vrtlIntrPortNum.description: Port number which will be connected to the Virtual Interface. Value zero meens that this virtual interface is not connected to any port.

vrtlIntrMinCellRate.name: vrtlIntrMinCellRate
vrtlIntrMinCellRate.description: Virtual Interface's minimum cell rate. The default value: for OC12 port is 1412832 cells/sec for OC3 port is 353208 cells/sec for T3 port is 96000 cells/sec for E3 port is 80000 cells/sec

vrtlIntrMaxCellRate.name: vrtlIntrMaxCellRate
vrtlIntrMaxCellRate.description: Virtual Interface's maximum cell rate. The default value: for OC12 port is 1412832 cells/sec for OC3 port is 353208 cells/sec for T3 port is 96000 cells/sec for E3 port is 80000 cells/sec

vrtlIntrCurrConfigPaths.name: vrtlIntrCurrConfigPaths
vrtlIntrCurrConfigPaths.description: This is not a configurable parameter. This gives the count of paths currently configured on this VI.

vrtlIntrCounterEntry.name: vrtlIntrCounterEntry
vrtlIntrCounterEntry.description: An entry in the Virtual Interface Counter Table.

vrtlIntrTotalCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrTotalCellCnt
vrtlIntrTotalCellCnt.description: Total number of cells (VC plus Qbin) that belong to this Virtual Interface.

vrtlIntrTotalQbinCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrTotalQbinCellCnt
vrtlIntrTotalQbinCellCnt.description: Total number of cells in the Qbin belonging to this Virtual Interface.

vrtlIntrRxdValidOAMCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdValidOAMCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdValidOAMCellCnt.description: Total number of OAM cell received.

vrtlIntrRxdRmCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdRmCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdRmCellCnt.description: Total number of RM cells Received.

vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-0 cells Received.

vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-1 cells Received.

vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedDiscardedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedDiscardedCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdClpUntaggedDiscardedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-0 cells discarded at Ingress.

vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedDiscardedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedDiscardedCellCnt
vrtlIntrRxdClpTaggedDiscardedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-1 cells discarded at Ingress.

vrtlIntrXmtdOAMCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrXmtdOAMCellCnt
vrtlIntrXmtdOAMCellCnt.description: Total number of OAM cells transmitted.

vrtlIntrXmtdRmCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrXmtdRmCellCnt
vrtlIntrXmtdRmCellCnt.description: Total number of RM cells transmitted.

vrtlIntrXmtdClpUntaggedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrXmtdClpUntaggedCellCnt
vrtlIntrXmtdClpUntaggedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-0 cells transmitted.

vrtlIntrXmtdClpTaggedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrXmtdClpTaggedCellCnt
vrtlIntrXmtdClpTaggedCellCnt.description: Total number of CLP-1 cells transmitted.

vrtlIntrQbinConfigEntry.name: vrtlIntrQbinConfigEntry
vrtlIntrQbinConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Virtual Interface Qbin Config Table.

queConfigVrtlIntrQbinNum.name: queConfigVrtlIntrQbinNum
queConfigVrtlIntrQbinNum.description: Virtual Interface Qbin Number. There are totaly 16 Qbin per Virtual Interface.

vrtlIntrQbinPri.name: vrtlIntrQbinPri
vrtlIntrQbinPri.description: This indicates the priority of the QBIN service within the Virtual Interface.

vrtlIntrQbinRate.name: vrtlIntrQbinRate
vrtlIntrQbinRate.description: The rate at which cells in the QBIN are serviced. Max Cell rate for OC3 interface is 353208 cell/sec.

vrtlIntrQbinDiscardSelection.name: vrtlIntrQbinDiscardSelection
vrtlIntrQbinDiscardSelection.description: Virtual Interface QBin Congestion control option.

vrtlIntrQbinMaxThreshold.name: vrtlIntrQbinMaxThreshold
vrtlIntrQbinMaxThreshold.description: Max cells that can be queued in the QBIN. The Get value will be different from the Set value because of FW internal round up.

vrtlIntrQbinClpHiThreshold.name: vrtlIntrQbinClpHiThreshold
vrtlIntrQbinClpHiThreshold.description: The threshold above which the tagged cells will be dropped. The Get value will be different from the Set value because of FW internal round up.

vrtlIntrQbinClpLoThreshold.name: vrtlIntrQbinClpLoThreshold
vrtlIntrQbinClpLoThreshold.description: Valid only if congestion control is set to CLP hysterises. The threshold upto which the dropping of the tagged cells should continue once it has crossed CLP HI threshold. The Get value will be different from the Set value because of FW internal round up.

vrtlIntrQbinFrameDiscardThreshold.name: vrtlIntrQbinFrameDiscardThreshold
vrtlIntrQbinFrameDiscardThreshold.description: Valid only if congestion control is set to Frame Discard. It is the threshold after which the QE will start discarding the entire frame if one or more cells of the frame is discarded.. The Get value will be different from the Set value because of FW internal round up.

vrtlIntrQbinEfciThreshold.name: vrtlIntrQbinEfciThreshold
vrtlIntrQbinEfciThreshold.description: The threshold above which the EFCI bits of the cell is set. The Get value will be different from the Set value because of FW internal round up.

vrtlIntrQbinCounterEntry.name: vrtlIntrQbinCounterEntry
vrtlIntrQbinCounterEntry.description: An entry in the Virtual Interface Qbin Counter Table.

queCounterVrtlIntrQbinNum.name: queCounterVrtlIntrQbinNum
queCounterVrtlIntrQbinNum.description: Virtual Interface Qbin Number. There are totaly 16 Qbin per Virtual Interface.

vrtlIntrQbinCurrentCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrQbinCurrentCellCnt
vrtlIntrQbinCurrentCellCnt.description: Total number of cells currently in the Qbin.

vrtlIntrQbinRxdCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrQbinRxdCellCnt
vrtlIntrQbinRxdCellCnt.description: Total number of cells arrived to the QBIN.

vrtlIntrQbinTxdCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrQbinTxdCellCnt
vrtlIntrQbinTxdCellCnt.description: Total number of cells departured from QBIN.

vrtlIntrQbinDiscardedCellCnt.name: vrtlIntrQbinDiscardedCellCnt
vrtlIntrQbinDiscardedCellCnt.description: Total number of arrivals to QBIN which were discarded.

rpmChanSlotNum.name: rpmChanSlotNum
rpmChanSlotNum.description: Specifies the slot number of the RPM card.

rpmChanInterface.name: rpmChanInterface
rpmChanInterface.description: This is the RPM's backplane interface. Currently there is only one interface.

rpmChanNum.name: rpmChanNum
rpmChanNum.description: This is the LCN. A unique number which identifies a connection. LCN maps VPI and VCI. For VCC, VCI range is 1..3825, and LCN range is 16..3840. LCN = VCI + 16. For VPC, VPI range is 1..255 and LCN range is 3841..4095. LCN = VPI + 3840.

rpmChanRowStatus.name: rpmChanRowStatus
rpmChanRowStatus.description: This indicates the status of this channel. 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY

rpmChanVcd.name: rpmChanVcd
rpmChanVcd.description: Virtual Circuit Descriptor. A unique number which identifies a connection.

rpmChanVpi.name: rpmChanVpi
rpmChanVpi.description: The VPI value for this channel. For VPC, VPI range is 1..255 and LCN range is 3841..4095. LCN = VPI + 3840

rpmChanVci.name: rpmChanVci
rpmChanVci.description: The VCI value for this channel. For VCC, VCI range is 1..3825, and LCN range is 16..3840. LCN = VCI + 16.

rpmChanSubInterface.name: rpmChanSubInterface
rpmChanSubInterface.description: This is the RPM's backplane sub-interface. (SNMP doent support index value 0) sub-interface starts from 1. The sub-interface 0 in CLI will be 1 here. So sub-interface is incremented by 1.

rpmChanLocalVpi.name: rpmChanLocalVpi
rpmChanLocalVpi.description: This VPI together with the local VCI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection. The VPI value is zero if it is a VCC conn. type.

rpmChanLocalVci.name: rpmChanLocalVci
rpmChanLocalVci.description: This VCI together with the local VPI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection.

rpmChanLocalNsap.name: rpmChanLocalNsap
rpmChanLocalNsap.description: The Near End NSAP Address value for this channel. This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as node name, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL Of the 13 bytes for the node name, only the first 8 bytes are used. If the node name is n (0 < n < 8) bytes long, the node name must be left justified ( Bytes 1 to n contain the node name and bytes (n+1) to 8 must be 0 ). Bytes 9-13 must be always 0.

rpmChanRemoteVpi.name: rpmChanRemoteVpi
rpmChanRemoteVpi.description: This VPI together with the remote VCI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection.

rpmChanRemoteVci.name: rpmChanRemoteVci
rpmChanRemoteVci.description: This VCI together with the remote VPI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection.

rpmChanRemoteNsap.name: rpmChanRemoteNsap
rpmChanRemoteNsap.description: The Far End NSAP Address value for this channel. This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL

rpmChanType.name: rpmChanType
rpmChanType.description: This specifies the connection type 1 ==> SVC 2 ==> PVC 3 ==> Soft PVC Currently only PVC is supported.

rpmChanConnType.name: rpmChanConnType
rpmChanConnType.description: This specifies the connection type 1 ==> Virtual Path Connection 2 ==> Virtual Channel Connection

rpmChanServiceType.name: rpmChanServiceType
rpmChanServiceType.description: This specifies the service type 1 ==> Constant Bit Rate 2 ==> Variable Bit Rate 4 ==> Unspecified Bit Rate 5 ==> ATM frame relay 6 ==> standard ABR 7 ==> foresight ABR Only VBR,standard ABR and UBR are supported in phase I.

rpmChanMastership.name: rpmChanMastership
rpmChanMastership.description: This specifies which end of the connection is the master. This is used by PXM to determine if this end point is master or slave. Only in AXIS shelf, 'unknown' is always used. For consistency it was added here.

rpmChanRtePriority.name: rpmChanRtePriority
rpmChanRtePriority.description: This is also known as class of service, it is used by PXM to determine how important this connection is when selecting connections to route.

rpmChanMaxCost.name: rpmChanMaxCost
rpmChanMaxCost.description: Maximum allowed cost. It is related to Cost Based Routing. This is used by PXM so that it won't choose a path with a cost greater than this configured level.

rpmChanRestrictTrkType.name: rpmChanRestrictTrkType
rpmChanRestrictTrkType.description: Restricted trunk type for routing, used by PXM. It specifies that the connection either cannot be routed over satellite trunks or terrestrial trunks, or it can be on any type of trunk.

rpmChanPCR.name: rpmChanPCR
rpmChanPCR.description: Peak cell rate.(in cells per sec.)

rpmChanRemotePCR.name: rpmChanRemotePCR
rpmChanRemotePCR.description: Peak cell rate of the other end, if not set, will be set to the same as local end PCR.

rpmChanMCR.name: rpmChanMCR
rpmChanMCR.description: Minimum cell rate.(in cells per sec.)

rpmChanRemoteMCR.name: rpmChanRemoteMCR
rpmChanRemoteMCR.description: Minimum cell rate of the other end, if not set, will be set to the same as local end MCR.

rpmChanPercentUtil.name: rpmChanPercentUtil
rpmChanPercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by this end-point.

rpmChanRemotePercentUtil.name: rpmChanRemotePercentUtil
rpmChanRemotePercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by the other end-point. If this is not specified in the connection setup request, it'll be set to be the same as the local end.

rpmChanEncapType.name: rpmChanEncapType
rpmChanEncapType.description: ATM adaptation layer (AAL) and Encapsulation type. aal5snap - LLC/SNAP precedes the protocol datagram. aal34smds - Encapsulation for SMDS network. aal5nlpid - Encapsulation that allows ATM interfaces to interoperate with HSSI. qsaal - signaling type PVC used for setting up or tearing down SVCs. ilmi - used to set up communication with ILMI. aal5mux[protocol] - a MUX-type Virtual circuit. ppp - PPP over ATM. The Encapsulation types aal34smds, qsaal and ilmi are not supported.

rpmChanMidLow.name: rpmChanMidLow
rpmChanMidLow.description: Starting Message Identifier Number for this PVC.

rpmChanMidHigh.name: rpmChanMidHigh
rpmChanMidHigh.description: Ending Message Identifier Number for this PVC.

rpmChanBurstSize.name: rpmChanBurstSize
rpmChanBurstSize.description: The Maximum number of ATM cells the virtual circuit can transmit.

rpmChanInArpFreq.name: rpmChanInArpFreq
rpmChanInArpFreq.description: Specifies how often (in minutes) Inverse ARP datagrams will be sent on this virtual circuit.

rpmChanOAMloopback.name: rpmChanOAMloopback
rpmChanOAMloopback.description: Specifies how often (in seconds) to generate an OAM F5 loopback cell from this virtual circuit.

rpmChanState.name: rpmChanState
rpmChanState.description: This indicates the status of this channel. 1 ==> notConfigured 2 ==> active 3 ==> failed. Currently 'failed' state is not supported. When the channel is not added, the state is notConfigured.

rpmChanVirtualTemplate.name: rpmChanVirtualTemplate
rpmChanVirtualTemplate.description: Specifies the Virtual Template used for CISCO PPP. If it is not using Virtual Template then this value is 0.

rpmChanAbrRDF.name: rpmChanAbrRDF
rpmChanAbrRDF.description: This is valid only for ABR Service Type. Rate Decrease Factor: Controls the rate decrease which occurs when backward RM-cells with CI=1 are received. Larger values lead to faster rate decrease. Reference - ATM Forum Traffic Management Specification Version 4.0 Section 5.10.2

rpmChanAbrRIF.name: rpmChanAbrRIF
rpmChanAbrRIF.description: This is valid only for ABR Service Type. Rate Increase Factor: Controls the rate increase which occurs when a backward RM-cell is received with CI=0 and NI=0. Larger values lead to faster rate increase. Reference - ATM Forum Traffic Management Specification Version 4.0 Section 5.10.2

rpmPortEntry.name: rpmPortEntry
rpmPortEntry.description: An entry for the RPM backplane sub interface. Each entry contains RPM's backplane sub interface number, its IP address and ATM address.

rpmPortSlotNum.name: rpmPortSlotNum
rpmPortSlotNum.description: Specifies the slot number of the RPM card.

rpmPortInterface.name: rpmPortInterface
rpmPortInterface.description: This is the RPM's backplane interface. Currently there is only one interface.

rpmPortSubInterface.name: rpmPortSubInterface
rpmPortSubInterface.description: It identifies a sub-interface. (SNMP doent support index value 0) sub-interface starts from 1. The sub-interface 0 in CLI will be 1 here. So sub-interface is incremented by 1.

rpmPortRowStatus.name: rpmPortRowStatus
rpmPortRowStatus.description: This indicates the status of this sub-interface. 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY

rpmPortState.name: rpmPortState
rpmPortState.description: This indicates the state of this sub-interface. 1 ==> notConfigured 2 ==> active 3 ==> failed. Currently 'failed' state is not supported.

rpmIfCnfRscPartTable.name: rpmIfCnfRscPartTable
rpmIfCnfRscPartTable.description: The table is for RPM interface resource partition.

rpmIfCnfRscPartEntry.name: rpmIfCnfRscPartEntry
rpmIfCnfRscPartEntry.description: An entry for a logical interface

rpmIfRscSlotNum.name: rpmIfRscSlotNum
rpmIfRscSlotNum.description: Specifies the slot number of the RPM card.

rpmIfRscPartIfNum.name: rpmIfRscPartIfNum
rpmIfRscPartIfNum.description: This is backplane interface number. Currently there is only one interface.

rpmIfRscPartCtrlrNum.name: rpmIfRscPartCtrlrNum
rpmIfRscPartCtrlrNum.description: This is index for controller using the interface . 1 - PAR 2 - PNNI 3 - TAG

rpmIfRscPrtRowStatus.name: rpmIfRscPrtRowStatus
rpmIfRscPrtRowStatus.description: This will add, delete or modify the partition. 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY

rpmIfRscPrtIngrPctBandwidth.name: rpmIfRscPrtIngrPctBandwidth
rpmIfRscPrtIngrPctBandwidth.description: The percentage of logical interface bandwidth.

rpmIfRscPrtEgrPctBandwidth.name: rpmIfRscPrtEgrPctBandwidth
rpmIfRscPrtEgrPctBandwidth.description: The percentage of logical interface bandwidth.

rpmIfRscPrtVpiLow.name: rpmIfRscPrtVpiLow
rpmIfRscPrtVpiLow.description: The beginning of the VPI range reserved for this partition.

rpmIfRscPrtVpiHigh.name: rpmIfRscPrtVpiHigh
rpmIfRscPrtVpiHigh.description: The end of the VPI range reserved for this partition.

rpmIfRscPrtVciLow.name: rpmIfRscPrtVciLow
rpmIfRscPrtVciLow.description: The beginning of the VCI range reserved for this partition. This field is only valid for logical interfaces configured with a single VPI.

rpmIfRscPrtVciHigh.name: rpmIfRscPrtVciHigh
rpmIfRscPrtVciHigh.description: The end of the VCI range reserved for this partition. This field is only valid for logical interfaces configured with a single VPI.

rpmIfRscPrtMaxChans.name: rpmIfRscPrtMaxChans
rpmIfRscPrtMaxChans.description: This represents no. of channels that are available to the controller.

parSnNodeId.name: parSnNodeId
parSnNodeId.description: This object specifies the node number of the node. When the network manager tries to modify the value of this object, a message is sent node state machine which propagates this information and the value gets modified only if the new node number is successfully propagated. The node number uniquely identifies a routing node in a network.

parSnNodeIP.name: parSnNodeIP
parSnNodeIP.description: This object specifies the IP address for routing node and is used for communication with SV+.

parSnNodeName.name: parSnNodeName
parSnNodeName.description: This object specifies the name of the node and is unique among all the nodes in the network. Whenever the name of the node is changed, AutoRoute has to propagate the information to the other nodes in the network. It also specifies the name of a PAR Feeder node.

parSnRevision.name: parSnRevision
parSnRevision.description: This object specifies the primary revision of the PAR running on the node. Format: cc.c.cc Where: c = one ascii character

parSnNodeAlarmStatus.name: parSnNodeAlarmStatus
parSnNodeAlarmStatus.description: This object specifies the type of alarm on the node. If there is no alarm the value of this object is none(1). If there is a minor alarm the value of this object is min(2) If there is a major alarm the value of this object is maj(3). If the node is unreachable the value of this object is unreach(4).

parSnNumberOfTrunks.name: parSnNumberOfTrunks
parSnNumberOfTrunks.description: This object specifies the number of trunks attached to the node.

parIfTable.name: parIfTable
parIfTable.description: Table of all logical interfaces supported by PAR

parIfLogicalInterface.name: parIfLogicalInterface
parIfLogicalInterface.description: This object specifies the logical interface number assigned by Platform Software

parIfType.name: parIfType
parIfType.description: Specifies the type of interface - uni, nni or clock. uni(1) interface is for user ports and trunks may be either nni or uni. Default type of the interface is uni(1) and it can be configured to nni(2) provided there are no connections on the port. Type of interface can be changed from nni(2) to uni(1) if the trunk is not added. clock type interface is one which is used derive the clock.

parIfOperStatus.name: parIfOperStatus
parIfOperStatus.description: This object specifies the operation status of the interface. For interfaces of type uni(1) the status is either up(1) or failed(3) as reported by platform. For interfaces of type nni(2) the status is either of up(1), added(2), failed(3) or added-failed(4). Status up(1) indicates that the interface is configured as trunk but the trunk is not added. Status failed(3) indicates that the interface is configured as trunk, the trunk is not added and platform indicates an alarm on the interface. Status added(2) indicates that the interface is configured as trunk and the trunk is added. Status added-failed(4) indicates that the interface is configured as trunk, the trunk is added and there is an alarm on the trunk. This alarm could be generated by PAR or reported by Platform.

parIfTxBw.name: parIfTxBw
parIfTxBw.description: This object specifies the transmit bandwidth for the interface in units of cells per second.

parIfRxBw.name: parIfRxBw
parIfRxBw.description: This object specifies the receive bandwidth for the interface in units of cells per second.

parIfMaxConn.name: parIfMaxConn
parIfMaxConn.description: This object specifies the maximum number of connections that can be configured over the interface.
