ausmLocalVpi.description: This VPI has different meaning with the end point VPI (CPE), it can be same with the end point VPI but not necessary, it represents the local end point VPI, this object is read only, therefore, SM is responsible to assign a value to it.

ausmLocalVci.name: ausmLocalVci
ausmLocalVci.description: This VCI has different meaning with the end point VCI (CPE), it can be same with the end point VPI but not necessary it represents the local end point VCI, this object is read only, therefore, SM is responsible to assign a value to it.

ausmLocalNSAP.name: ausmLocalNSAP
ausmLocalNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 2 bytes rsvd, 2 bytes for slot (5 bits) and port number (11 bits), and 1 byte for SEL

ausmRemoteVpi.name: ausmRemoteVpi
ausmRemoteVpi.description: This VPI has different with the remote end point VPI (CPE), this is similar to a connection ID and it can be same with the remote end point VPI but not necessary

ausmRemoteVci.name: ausmRemoteVci
ausmRemoteVci.description: This VCI has different with the remote end point VCI (CPE), this is similar to a connection ID and it can be same with the remote end point VPI but not necessary

ausmRemoteNSAP.name: ausmRemoteNSAP
ausmRemoteNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 2 bytes rsvd, 2 bytes for slot (5 bits) and port number (11 bits), and 1 byte for SEL

ausmMastership.name: ausmMastership
ausmMastership.description: This is used by PXM to determine if this end point is master or slave. In AXIS shelf, unknown is always used, but in MGX shelf, if unknown is set, PXM will fail the set request.

ausmVpcFlag.name: ausmVpcFlag
ausmVpcFlag.description: This represents the connection type, used for PXM to identify VPC/VCC

ausmConnServiceType.name: ausmConnServiceType
ausmConnServiceType.description: This specifies the service type 1 ==> Constant Bit Rate 2 ==> Variable Bit Rate 3 ==> Not used 4 ==> Unspecified Bit Rate 5 ==> ATM frame relay 6 ==> standard ABR 7 ==> foresight ABR 8 ==> Real-Time Variable Bit Rate Note that this is used by PXM card, FRSM doesn't need to set it Also to make it compatible with existing AUSM MIB definition, value 3 is not used. The following types are being added for PNNI support. and are based on UNI 4.0 cbr1 (21) - CBR.1 vbr1rt (22) - Real time VBR.1 vbr2rt (23) - Real time VBR.2 vbr3rt (24) - Real time VBR.3 vbr1nrt(25) - Non Real time VBR.1 vbr2nrt(26) - Non Real time VBR.2 vbr3nrt(27) - Non Real time VBR.3 ubr1 (28) - UBR.1 ubr2 (29) - UBR.2 stdabr (30) - TM 4.0 compliant standard ABR cbr2 (31) - CBR.2 cbr3 (32) - CBR.3

ausmRoutingPriority.name: ausmRoutingPriority
ausmRoutingPriority.description: This is also known as class of service, it is used by PXM to determine how important this connection is when selecting connections to route

ausmMaxCost.name: ausmMaxCost
ausmMaxCost.description: Maximum allowed cost. It is related to Cost Based Routing. This is used by PXM so that it won't choose a path with a cost greater than this configured level. When used with PAR controller the valid range is 1..65535 and the default value is 255. When used with PNNI controller the valid range is 1..2147483647 and the default value is 2147483647.

ausmRestrictTrunkType.name: ausmRestrictTrunkType
ausmRestrictTrunkType.description: Restricted trunk type for routing, used by PXM. It specifies that the connection either cannot be routed over satelite trunks, or terrestrial trunks, or it can be on any type of trunk.

ausmConnPCR.name: ausmConnPCR
ausmConnPCR.description: Peak cell rate, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

ausmConnMCR.name: ausmConnMCR
ausmConnMCR.description: Minimum cell rate, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

ausmConnPercentUtil.name: ausmConnPercentUtil
ausmConnPercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by theis end-point.

ausmConnRemotePCR.name: ausmConnRemotePCR
ausmConnRemotePCR.description: Peak cell rate of the other end, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

ausmConnRemoteMCR.name: ausmConnRemoteMCR
ausmConnRemoteMCR.description: Minimum cell rate of the other end, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

ausmConnRemotePercentUtil.name: ausmConnRemotePercentUtil
ausmConnRemotePercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by the other end-point.

ausmConnForeSightEnable.name: ausmConnForeSightEnable
ausmConnForeSightEnable.description: This object is used by the controller(PAR/PNNI/TAG) to set up the Qbin for the connection

ausmConnFGCRAEnable.name: ausmConnFGCRAEnable
ausmConnFGCRAEnable.description: enables/disables Frame based GCRA (early packet discard).

ausmChanReroute.name: ausmChanReroute
ausmChanReroute.description: This is used by the administrator to trigger the re-routing of the connection. The rerouting takes effect, when this object is set to true(1). When set to false (2), no action is taken. A get on this object always returns false (2). This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

ausmConnSCR.name: ausmConnSCR
ausmConnSCR.description: Sustained cell rate, Used for VBR connections setup with PNNI controller.

ausmConnRemoteSCR.name: ausmConnRemoteSCR
ausmConnRemoteSCR.description: Sustained cell rate of the other end, Used for VBR connections setup with PNNI controller.

ausmConnMBS.name: ausmConnMBS
ausmConnMBS.description: Maximum burst size, Used for VBR connections setup with PNNI controller. In MGX switches, release 3.0.0.0 and above, the default value is 1024

ausmConnRemoteMBS.name: ausmConnRemoteMBS
ausmConnRemoteMBS.description: Maximum burst size at the remote end of the connection, Used for VBR connections setup with PNNI controller.

ausmConnTemplateId.name: ausmConnTemplateId
ausmConnTemplateId.description: This object specifies the template identifier for the connection template associated with this connection. The valid range for templates is 1..16. A value of 17 indicates no template is associated with this connection

ausmConnAdminStatus.name: ausmConnAdminStatus
ausmConnAdminStatus.description: This object specifies channel admin status. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

ausmChanNumNextAvailable.name: ausmChanNumNextAvailable
ausmChanNumNextAvailable.description: This variable contains the next unused channel number of the possible 1000. This number can be used in channel config table. ChanNumNextAvailable gets updated whenever this number is used to create a new logical channel. Value 0 for this variable indicates that no more channels are available. In AUSM (4-port card), the maximum number of values for this variable is 256 (i.e. 16 ..271).

ausmChanVpIdNextAvailable.name: ausmChanVpIdNextAvailable
ausmChanVpIdNextAvailable.description: This variable contains the next unused local VPId of the possible 1 to 100. This number can be used in channel config table. It gets updated if the number is used to create a new vp connection. There can max 100 vp connections per slot. Value of 0 for this variable indicates that no more vp connections are available.

ausmStdABRCnfGrpTable.name: ausmStdABRCnfGrpTable
ausmStdABRCnfGrpTable.description: The ABR config table is for logical channel interface there are 1000 entries for the 8 logical ports in AUSM (8-port).

ausmStdABRCnfChanNum.name: ausmStdABRCnfChanNum
ausmStdABRCnfChanNum.description: Refers to the virtual connection index.

ausmStdABRType.name: ausmStdABRType
ausmStdABRType.description: StdabrType of value 1 indicates a TM4.0 switch behaving connection (Transparent connection) which assumes that RM cells will be received from a TM4.0 compliant CPE. Value 2 indicates a TM4.0 source destination behaving connection (Terminating connection) which generates RM cells by itself.

ausmStdABRTBE.name: ausmStdABRTBE
ausmStdABRTBE.description: Transient Buffer Exposure. The unit is number of cells.

ausmStdABRFRTT.name: ausmStdABRFRTT
ausmStdABRFRTT.description: Fixed Round-Trip Time. The unit is milliseconds. Value 0 signifies that FRTT value is not available.

ausmStdABRRDF.name: ausmStdABRRDF
ausmStdABRRDF.description: Rate Decrease Factor. This unitless value has to be inversed to arrive at the actual value. The valid values possible are only powers of 2; i.e. 1, 2, 4, 8 ..... 32768 . The SNMP agent has to verify this compliance.

ausmStdABRRIF.name: ausmStdABRRIF
ausmStdABRRIF.description: Rate Increase Factor. This unitless value has to be inversed to arrive at the actual value. The valid values possible are are only powers of 2; i.e. 1, 2, 4, 8 ..... 32768 . The SNMP agent has to verify this compliance.

ausmStdABRNrm.name: ausmStdABRNrm
ausmStdABRNrm.description: Maximum number of cells a source may send for each forward RM cell. The valid values possible are only powers of 2 starting from 2 ; i.e. 2, 4, 8 ..... 256. The SNMP agent has to verify this compliance.

ausmStdABRTrm.name: ausmStdABRTrm
ausmStdABRTrm.description: Upper bound on the time between forward RM cells for an active source. The unit is in milliseconds.

ausmStdABRCDF.name: ausmStdABRCDF
ausmStdABRCDF.description: Cutoff Decrease Factor. This unitless value has to be inversed to arrive at the actual value. The valid values possible are 0 and only powers of 2; i.e. 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64 . The SNMP agent has to verify this compliance.

ausmStdABRADTF.name: ausmStdABRADTF
ausmStdABRADTF.description: ACR Decrease Time Factor. Unit of this value is milliseconds. Granularity allowed is 10 milli seconds. The SNMP agent has to verify this compliance.

ausmStdABRICR.name: ausmStdABRICR
ausmStdABRICR.description: Initial cell Rate. The actual value depends on the speed of the logical port (which can be a T1, E1 (normal), E1 (clear), IMA T1, IMA T1, IMA E1 (normal) or IMA E1 (clear) port. Note that the IMA port's speed is variable and depends on the number of links in the port.

ausmStdABRMCR.name: ausmStdABRMCR
ausmStdABRMCR.description: Minimum cell Rate. The actual value depends on the speed of the logical port (which can be a T1, E1 (normal), E1 (clear), IMA T1 IMA E1 (normal) or IMA E1 (clear) port. Note that the IMA port's speed is variable and depends on the number of links in the port. Please note that the MCR value will include bandwidth occupied by Data cells as well as all in-rate RM cells.

ausmStdABRPCR.name: ausmStdABRPCR
ausmStdABRPCR.description: Peak cell Rate. The actual value depends on the speed of the logical port (which can be a T1, E1 (normal), E1 (clear), IMA T1 IMA E1 (normal) or IMA E1 (clear) port. Note that the IMA port's speed is variable and depends on the number of links in the port. Please note that the PCR value will include bandwidth occupied by Data cells as well as all in-rate RM cells.

ausmChanCntGrpTable.name: ausmChanCntGrpTable
ausmChanCntGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical channel interface there are 1000 entries for 8 logical ports. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is synonymous with a physical port and the number of supported entries in this table is 256.

ausmCntChanNum.name: ausmCntChanNum
ausmCntChanNum.description: Refers to the logical channel number. In AUSM (4-port card), the permissible range is from 16..271.

chanSecInService.name: chanSecInService
chanSecInService.description: The number of seconds channel is in service

chanCongestMinutes.name: chanCongestMinutes
chanCongestMinutes.description: The number of minutes for which congestion was experienced

chanIngrPeakQDepth.name: chanIngrPeakQDepth
chanIngrPeakQDepth.description: Peak queue depth on the ingress direction

chanIngrRcvCells.name: chanIngrRcvCells
chanIngrRcvCells.description: The number of cells received in the Ingress direction

chanIngrClpSetRcvCells.name: chanIngrClpSetRcvCells
chanIngrClpSetRcvCells.description: The number of CLP set cells received in Ingress direction

chanIngrEfciSetRcvCells.name: chanIngrEfciSetRcvCells
chanIngrEfciSetRcvCells.description: The number of EFCI set cells received in Ingress direction

chanIngrQfullDiscardCells.name: chanIngrQfullDiscardCells
chanIngrQfullDiscardCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to ingress Q full

chanIngrClpSetDiscardCells.name: chanIngrClpSetDiscardCells
chanIngrClpSetDiscardCells.description: The number of CLP set cells discarded in Ingress direction

chanIngrUpcClpSetCells.name: chanIngrUpcClpSetCells
chanIngrUpcClpSetCells.description: The number of cells for which CLP was set by UPC

chanIngrXmtCells.name: chanIngrXmtCells
chanIngrXmtCells.description: The number of cells transmitted to the cellbus

chanShelfAlarmDiscardCells.name: chanShelfAlarmDiscardCells
chanShelfAlarmDiscardCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to Shelf Alarm

ausmChanClrButton.name: ausmChanClrButton
ausmChanClrButton.description: writing a value of 2 resets all the counters

chanEpdDiscCells.name: chanEpdDiscCells
chanEpdDiscCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to EPD (Early Packet Discard) condition

chanPpdDiscCells.name: chanPpdDiscCells
chanPpdDiscCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to PPD (Partial Packet Discard) condition

chanIngrRcvCellRate.name: chanIngrRcvCellRate
chanIngrRcvCellRate.description: The number of cells received per second from the port. Statistics collected before UPC and ingress qeueing. The maximum value is 5000 because clear E1 rate is 4830.

chanIngrRcvUtilization.name: chanIngrRcvUtilization
chanIngrRcvUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the reserved bandwidth (PCR). Statistics collected before UPC and ingress queueing. The maximum value is 200 because a connection can oversubcribe.

chanIngrXmtCellRate.name: chanIngrXmtCellRate
chanIngrXmtCellRate.description: The number of cells transmitted per second to the network. Statistics collected after UPC and ingress qeueing.

chanIngrXmtUtilization.name: chanIngrXmtUtilization
chanIngrXmtUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the reserved bandwidth (PCR). Statistics collected after UPC and ingress queueing.

chanEgrRcvCellRate.name: chanEgrRcvCellRate
chanEgrRcvCellRate.description: The number of cells received per second from the network. Statistics collected before egress qeueing.

chanEgrRcvUtilization.name: chanEgrRcvUtilization
chanEgrRcvUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the reserved bandwidth (PCR). Statistics collected before egress queueing.

chanIngrXmtAAL5Frames.name: chanIngrXmtAAL5Frames
chanIngrXmtAAL5Frames.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of AAL5 Frames that are sent to the network

chanIngrEfciSetXmtCells.name: chanIngrEfciSetXmtCells
chanIngrEfciSetXmtCells.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of EFCI set cells that are transmitted to the network. This statistis is collected after the policing and queueing.

chanEgrPortQfullDiscardCells.name: chanEgrPortQfullDiscardCells
chanEgrPortQfullDiscardCells.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of cells discarded because of Egress Port Queue full. This count is displayed for the queue corresponding to port and the service type to which this channel belongs.

chanEgrPortQClpThresDiscardCells.name: chanEgrPortQClpThresDiscardCells
chanEgrPortQClpThresDiscardCells.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of cells discarded because of Egress Port Queue CLP Threshold exceed. This count is displayed for the queue corresponding to port and the service type to which this channel belongs.

chanTxFifoFullCnt.name: chanTxFifoFullCnt
chanTxFifoFullCnt.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of times the AUSM card tried to send a cell, but was unable to send because the Transmit FIFO was full. Note that this is NOT a count of the number of cells dropped. This statistics is per card statistics.

chanIngrCurrQDepth.name: chanIngrCurrQDepth
chanIngrCurrQDepth.description: Current queue depth on the ingress direction

ausmChanStateGrpTable.name: ausmChanStateGrpTable
ausmChanStateGrpTable.description: Table of transmit/receive states of channels.

ausmStateChanNum.name: ausmStateChanNum
ausmStateChanNum.description: Refers to the logical channel number. In AUSM (4-port card), the permissible range is from 16..271.

ausmChanState.name: ausmChanState
ausmChanState.description: This variable indicates the state of the VC (channel) failed(4) is added to distinguish between alarm (when the connection segment is not actually broken) and failed(when the segment is actually broken). This is applicable only to the PNNI environment.

chanEgrXmtState.name: chanEgrXmtState
chanEgrXmtState.description: indicates the status of port transmit(Egress)

chanIngrRcvState.name: chanIngrRcvState
chanIngrRcvState.description: indicates the status of port receive(Ingress)

chanIngrXmtState.name: chanIngrXmtState
chanIngrXmtState.description: This variable indicates the transmit state of the VC (channel) on the Cellbus side (Ingress) 1 - other 2- normal 3 - sendingAIS 4 - sendingFerf

chanEgrRcvState.name: chanEgrRcvState
chanEgrRcvState.description: This variable indicates the receiving state of the VC (channel) on the Cellbus side (Egress) 1 - other 2- normal 3 - receivingAIS 4 - receivingFERF

ausmChanStatusBitMap.name: ausmChanStatusBitMap
ausmChanStatusBitMap.description: This variable indicates the consolidated bit map of the channel alarm state. Individual bit positions are as defined below. Bit position Fail/Alarm Reason ------------ ---------- ------ 0 Alarm port side AIS/RDI Rx 1 Alarm n/w side AIS/RDI Rx 2 Fail Conditioned(A bit from n/w) 3 Alarm Reserved 4 Fail Reserved 5 Fail Reserved 6 Alarm Reserved 7 Alarm Reserved Fail bitmap mask : 0x34 Alarm bitmap mask: 0xCB This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

ausmEndPointMapGrpTable.name: ausmEndPointMapGrpTable
ausmEndPointMapGrpTable.description: For Ausm-4p There are 255 entries For Ausm-8p There are 1000 entries For PXM (MGX) There are 4096 entries Port Num and VpiVci will uniquely identify a row.

ausmEndPortNum.name: ausmEndPortNum
ausmEndPortNum.description: Refers to the logical port on the board. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is synonymous with a physical port. In PXM, a port refers to the Logical Broadband Interface. Refer bbIfCnfPortGrp.my for more information.

endVpi.name: endVpi
endVpi.description: The VPI value for the connection

endVci.name: endVci
endVci.description: The VCI value for the connection

ausmEndChanNum.name: ausmEndChanNum
ausmEndChanNum.description: Refers to the logical connection for this port and VpiVci. In AUSM (4-port card), the permissible range is 16..271 In AUSM (8-port card), the permissible range is 16..1015 In PXM (MGX ) , the permissible range is 16..4111

endChanType.name: endChanType
endChanType.description: Refers to the type of the connection for this Port and VpiVci

ausmPortCnfPortGrpTable.name: ausmPortCnfPortGrpTable
ausmPortCnfPortGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical port interface there are 8 entries for either T1 or E1

ausmPortCnfPortGrpEntry.name: ausmPortCnfPortGrpEntry
ausmPortCnfPortGrpEntry.description: An entry for logical port. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

ausmPortNum.name: ausmPortNum
ausmPortNum.description: This is logical port number. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

portEnable.name: portEnable
portEnable.description: This variable enables or disables the port 1 - disable 2 - enable

ausmPortType.name: ausmPortType
ausmPortType.description: This variable indicates whether UNI/NNI/STI interface STI mode is supported only in IMATM. vpTrkUni should be used only in IMATM when virtual trunks are passing through IMATM (i.e. the cell format is UNI but ForeSight information is carried in the lower 16 bits)

ausmPortIfType.name: ausmPortIfType
ausmPortIfType.description: This variable indicates the type of interface

ausmPortSpeed.name: ausmPortSpeed
ausmPortSpeed.description: The speed of the port in cells per second

ausmLineNum.name: ausmLineNum
ausmLineNum.description: The line number associated with the logical port. For AUSM (4 port), the line number is same as the logical port. In AUSM-8p, these two can be different

ausmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.name: ausmPortCnfResPartGrpTable
ausmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical port interface there are 4/8 entries for either T1 or E1 or AIMUX ports For PXM (MGX), there are 32 entries.

ausmResPartPortNum.name: ausmResPartPortNum
ausmResPartPortNum.description: This is logical port number In PXM, a port refers to the Logical Broadband Interface. Refer bbIfCnfPortGrp.my for more information.

ausmPortSvcInUse.name: ausmPortSvcInUse
ausmPortSvcInUse.description: Setting this object to 1 indicates that the resources (LCN/Local VPID/VCI/VPI) have been partitioned and INS and SV+ are currently using this information. The resource partition information can be changed after setting this variable to 2. The default value is 2 (NotInUse).

ausmPortSvcShareLcnVpid.name: ausmPortSvcShareLcnVpid
ausmPortSvcShareLcnVpid.description: Indicates whether or not the LCN and VPid address spaces are shared across all the ports. Default value is 2 (cardBased).

ausmPortSvcLcnLow.name: ausmPortSvcLcnLow
ausmPortSvcLcnLow.description: The beginning of the LCN range reserved for SVCs. Both the LCN low and high values apply to all ports when the 'atmPortSvcShareLcnVpid' object is set to 2 (CardBased). When they are changed for one port the change is applicable/propagated to all ports.

ausmPortSvcLcnHigh.name: ausmPortSvcLcnHigh
ausmPortSvcLcnHigh.description: The end of the LCN range reserved for SVCs.

ausmPortSvcVpidLow.name: ausmPortSvcVpidLow
ausmPortSvcVpidLow.description: The beginning of the VPID range reserved for SVCs. Both the VPID low and high values apply to all ports when the 'atmPortSvcShareLcnVpid' object is set to 2 (CardBased). When they are changed for one port the change is applicable/propagated to all ports.

ausmPortSvcVpidHigh.name: ausmPortSvcVpidHigh
ausmPortSvcVpidHigh.description: The end of the VPID range reserved for SVCs.

ausmPortSvcVciLow.name: ausmPortSvcVciLow
ausmPortSvcVciLow.description: The beginning of the VCI range reserved for SVCs. For VPI connections the valid VCI values are 0 - 4095

ausmPortSvcVciHigh.name: ausmPortSvcVciHigh
ausmPortSvcVciHigh.description: The end of the VCI range reserved for SVCs. For VPI connections the valid VCI values are 0 -4095

ausmPortSvcVpiLow.name: ausmPortSvcVpiLow
ausmPortSvcVpiLow.description: The beginning of the VCI range reserved for SVCs.

ausmPortSvcVpiHigh.name: ausmPortSvcVpiHigh
ausmPortSvcVpiHigh.description: The end of the VPI range reserved for SVCs.

ausmPortIngrSvcBandW.name: ausmPortIngrSvcBandW
ausmPortIngrSvcBandW.description: This represents Ingress Bandwidth reserved for SVC

ausmPortEgrSvcBandW.name: ausmPortEgrSvcBandW
ausmPortEgrSvcBandW.description: This represents Egress Bandwidth reserved for SVC

ausmPortDelSvcsGrpTable.name: ausmPortDelSvcsGrpTable
ausmPortDelSvcsGrpTable.description: The table is for logical port interface there are 4/8 entries for either T1 or E1 or AIMUX ports For PXM (MGX), there are 32 entries.

ausmDelSvcsPortNum.name: ausmDelSvcsPortNum
ausmDelSvcsPortNum.description: This is logical port number In PXM, a port refers to the Logical Broadband Interface. Refer bbIfCnfPortGrp.my for more information.

ausmPortDeleteSvcs.name: ausmPortDeleteSvcs
ausmPortDeleteSvcs.description: Setting this object to 1 indicates that all the SVC connections on the given port has to be deleted

ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpTable.name: ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpTable
ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpTable.description: In AUSM (4port): the Service queue table has 64 entries, 16 each for every port, in addition there are 4 queues for OAM/ILMI traffic In AUSM (8-port), the Service queue table has 128 entries, 16 each for every port, in addition there are 8 queues for OAM/ILMI traffic

ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpEntry.name: ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpEntry
ausmPortCnfServiceQueGrpEntry.description: An entry for a single queue

egrQIndex.name: egrQIndex
egrQIndex.description: Egress queue number. In AUSM (4 port), only range from 1..12 is permissible

servicePortNum.name: servicePortNum
servicePortNum.description: Logical port number to which egress queue is associated. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port. This is read only and queue mapping is as follows 1-16 port no 1 17-32 port no 2 33-48 port no 3 49-64 port no 4 For AUSM 8-port card, the following queue mapping is used in addition to the above: 65-80 port no 5 81-96 port no 6 97-112 port no 7 113-128 port no 8

egrQServiceSequence.name: egrQServiceSequence
egrQServiceSequence.description: Egress queue number sequence in the priority list. In AUSM (4 port), range from only 1..12 is permissible

egrQDepthMax.name: egrQDepthMax
egrQDepthMax.description: The maximum depth of the egress queue. In AUSM (4 port), range from only 1..8000 is permissible

egrQCLPThreshHigh.name: egrQCLPThreshHigh
egrQCLPThreshHigh.description: High CLP threshold of the egress queue. In AUSM (4 port), range from only 1..8000 is permissible.This value should be less than or equal to egrQDepthMax.

egrQCLPThreshLow.name: egrQCLPThreshLow
egrQCLPThreshLow.description: Low CLP threshold of the egress queue. In AUSM (4 port), range from only 1..8000 is permissible. This value should be less than or equal to egrQCLPThreshHigh.

egrQEfciThresh.name: egrQEfciThresh
egrQEfciThresh.description: Threshold of the egress queue for EFCI. In AUSM (4 port), range from only 1..8000 is permissible.This value should be less than or equal to egrQDepthMax.

egrQAlgorithm.name: egrQAlgorithm
egrQAlgorithm.description: The algorithm number for the Egress queue 1-5 are valid values 'ff'h is disable

egrMaxBwInc.name: egrMaxBwInc
egrMaxBwInc.description: The increment for the Maximum carry for the queue. In AUSM (8 port), range from only 1..511 is permissible

egrMinBwInc.name: egrMinBwInc
egrMinBwInc.description: The increment for the minimum carry for the queue. In AUSM (8 port), range from only 1..511 is permissible

egrQCLPState.name: egrQCLPState
egrQCLPState.description: this variable indicates the CLP state for the queue

egrQfullDiscardCells.name: egrQfullDiscardCells
egrQfullDiscardCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to Egress Q full

egrQClpSetDiscardCells.name: egrQClpSetDiscardCells
egrQClpSetDiscardCells.description: The number of CLP set cells discarded in Egress direction

ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpTable.name: ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpTable
ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpTable.description: The config table is for upto 8 logical port interfaces

ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpEntry.name: ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpEntry
ausmPortCnfSigILMIGrpEntry.description: An entry for a logical port. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

sigPortNum.name: sigPortNum
sigPortNum.description: Refers to the logical port index. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

ausmSignallingProtocolType.name: ausmSignallingProtocolType
ausmSignallingProtocolType.description: This will set the signalling protocol 1 - other 2 - noSignalling 3 - ILMI

signallingVpi.name: signallingVpi
signallingVpi.description: indicates the VPI on which signalling cells arrive

signallingVci.name: signallingVci
signallingVci.description: indicates the VCI on which signalling cells arrive

addrPrefix.name: addrPrefix
addrPrefix.description: Network Prefix for the ATM address

customerId.name: customerId
customerId.description: for the INS as a read/write variable

protocolRevNo.name: protocolRevNo
protocolRevNo.description: for the INS as a read/write variable

ausmPortCntPortGrpTable.name: ausmPortCntPortGrpTable
ausmPortCntPortGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical port interface there are 8 entries for either T1 or E1

ausmCntPortNum.name: ausmCntPortNum
ausmCntPortNum.description: This is the logical port number. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

ingrRcvCells.name: ingrRcvCells
ingrRcvCells.description: The number of cells received in Ingress direction

ingrGfcErrCells.name: ingrGfcErrCells
ingrGfcErrCells.description: The number of cells received in Ingress direction with non zero-GFC

ingrVpiVciErrCells.name: ingrVpiVciErrCells
ingrVpiVciErrCells.description: The number of cells received in Ingress direction with unknown VpiVci

ingrLastUnknVpiVci.name: ingrLastUnknVpiVci
ingrLastUnknVpiVci.description: The last unknown Vpi Vci value

egrXmtCells.name: egrXmtCells
egrXmtCells.description: The number of cells transmitted in the egress direction

egrPortAlarmDiscardCells.name: egrPortAlarmDiscardCells
egrPortAlarmDiscardCells.description: The number of cells discarded due to port alarm

egrXmtClpSetCells.name: egrXmtClpSetCells
egrXmtClpSetCells.description: The number of cells transmitted in Egress direction with CLP bit set

egrXmtEfciSetCells.name: egrXmtEfciSetCells
egrXmtEfciSetCells.description: The number of cells transmitted in Egress direction with EFCI bit set

portXmtAisCells.name: portXmtAisCells
portXmtAisCells.description: The number of AIS cells transmitted towards port

portXmtSgmtLpbkCells.name: portXmtSgmtLpbkCells
portXmtSgmtLpbkCells.description: The number of Segment Loopback cells transmitted towards port

portRcvAisCells.name: portRcvAisCells
portRcvAisCells.description: The number of AIS cells received in Ingress direction

portRcvFerfCells.name: portRcvFerfCells
portRcvFerfCells.description: The number of FERF cells received in Ingress direction

portRcvSgmtLpbkCells.name: portRcvSgmtLpbkCells
portRcvSgmtLpbkCells.description: The number of Segment Loopback cells received in Ingress direction

portRcvCrcErrOAMCells.name: portRcvCrcErrOAMCells
portRcvCrcErrOAMCells.description: The number of OAM cells received in Ingress direction with CRC error

ausmPortClrButton.name: ausmPortClrButton
ausmPortClrButton.description: writing a value of 2 resets all the counters

ingrRcvClpSetCells.name: ingrRcvClpSetCells
ingrRcvClpSetCells.description: The number of cells received from the port which had the CLP bit in the ATM cell header equal to 1.

ingrXmtCells.name: ingrXmtCells
ingrXmtCells.description: The number of cells out of the received cells from the port that were sent to the network. This count is taken after policing and ingress queueing.

egrRcvCells.name: egrRcvCells
egrRcvCells.description: The number of cells received from the network in the egress direction

ingrRcvCellRate.name: ingrRcvCellRate
ingrRcvCellRate.description: The number of cells received per second from the port in the ingress direction. Maximum value is 5000 because because clear E1 rate is 4830.

ingrRcvUtilization.name: ingrRcvUtilization
ingrRcvUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the port speed in the ingress direction.

egrXmtCellRate.name: egrXmtCellRate
egrXmtCellRate.description: The number of cells received transmitted to the port in the egress direction.

egrXmtUtilization.name: egrXmtUtilization
egrXmtUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the port speed in the egress direction.

egrRcvCellRate.name: egrRcvCellRate
egrRcvCellRate.description: The number of cells received per second from the network in the egress receive direction.

egrRcvUtilization.name: egrRcvUtilization
egrRcvUtilization.description: The percentage utilization of the port speed in the egress receive direction.

totalIngrQfulldiscardCells.name: totalIngrQfulldiscardCells
totalIngrQfulldiscardCells.description: The total number of cells dropped on all the channels on this port because the the ingress Q was full. Adds up all the IngressQfull discard per channel statistics for all the channels in the port.

txFifoFullCnt.name: txFifoFullCnt
txFifoFullCnt.description: This statistics provides a count of the number of times the AUSM card tried to send a cell, but was unable to send because the Transmit FIFO was full. Note that this is NOT a count of the number of cells dropped. This statistics is per card statistics. This counter is duplicated in channel count group to help monitoring.

totalIngrClpSetDiscardCells.name: totalIngrClpSetDiscardCells
totalIngrClpSetDiscardCells.description: The total number of cells with CLP=1 dropped on all the channels on this port because of either PCR Exceeded, SCR exceeded (with CLP tagging disabled) or CLP Hysteris. Adds up all the IngressClpSet discard per channel statistics for all the channels in the port.

ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpTable.name: ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpTable
ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpTable.description: The config table is for physical port interface there are 8 entries for either T1 or E1 or IMA

ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpEntry.name: ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpEntry
ausmPortCntSigILMIGrpEntry.description: An entry for logical port. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

sigCntPortNum.name: sigCntPortNum
sigCntPortNum.description: This is the logical port number.

snmpPduReceived.name: snmpPduReceived
snmpPduReceived.description: The number of snmp packets received

getRequestReceived.name: getRequestReceived
getRequestReceived.description: The number of get request messages received

getNextRequestReceived.name: getNextRequestReceived
getNextRequestReceived.description: The number of get-next messages received

setRequestReceived.name: setRequestReceived
setRequestReceived.description: The number of set messages received

getResponseReceived.name: getResponseReceived
getResponseReceived.description: The number of Keep Alive response messages received

getResponseTransmitted.name: getResponseTransmitted
getResponseTransmitted.description: The number of response messages transmitted

getRequestTransmitted.name: getRequestTransmitted
getRequestTransmitted.description: The number of Keep Alive get request messages transmitted

trapTransmitted.name: trapTransmitted
trapTransmitted.description: The number of trap messages transmitted

invalidPDUReceived.name: invalidPDUReceived
invalidPDUReceived.description: The number of invalid PDUs received

asn1ParseError.name: asn1ParseError
asn1ParseError.description: The number of parse errors on ASN.1

noSuchNameError.name: noSuchNameError
noSuchNameError.description: The number of errors for name not present

tooBigError.name: tooBigError
tooBigError.description: The number of messages received with len > 484

portSigClrButton.name: portSigClrButton
portSigClrButton.description: writing a value of 2 resets all the counters

ausmPortStateGrpTable.name: ausmPortStateGrpTable
ausmPortStateGrpTable.description: The state table for the port interface there are 8 entries for either T1 or E1 or IMA.

ausmPortStateGrpEntry.name: ausmPortStateGrpEntry
ausmPortStateGrpEntry.description: An entry for logical port. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

ausmStatePortNum.name: ausmStatePortNum
ausmStatePortNum.description: This is logical port number. In AUSM (4-port card), a logical port is same as a physical port.

ausmPortState.name: ausmPortState
ausmPortState.description: This variable indicates the status of the port

ausmPortOversubscribed.name: ausmPortOversubscribed
ausmPortOversubscribed.description: This variable indicates the whether the port is over subscribed or not

ausmPortIngrPercentUtil.name: ausmPortIngrPercentUtil
ausmPortIngrPercentUtil.description: Percentage Utilization of the Port in the Ingress direction.

ausmPortEgrPercentUtil.name: ausmPortEgrPercentUtil
ausmPortEgrPercentUtil.description: Percentage Utilization of the Port in the Egress direction.

ausmInterfaceConfTable.name: ausmInterfaceConfTable
ausmInterfaceConfTable.description: This table contains ATM local interface configuration parameters, one entry per ATM (ausm) interface port.

ausmInterfaceConfEntry.name: ausmInterfaceConfEntry
ausmInterfaceConfEntry.description: This list contains ATM interface configuration parameters and state variables and is indexed by ausmInterfacePortNum values of ATM interfaces.

ausmInterfacePortNum.name: ausmInterfacePortNum
ausmInterfacePortNum.description: This is logical port number. In AUSM, a logical port is same as a physical port.

ausmInterfaceMyNeighborIpAddress.name: ausmInterfaceMyNeighborIpAddress
ausmInterfaceMyNeighborIpAddress.description: The IP address of the neighbor system connected to the far end of this interface, to which a Network Management Station can send SNMP messages, as IP datagrams sent to UDP port 161, in order to access network management information concerning the operation of that system. Note that the value of this object may be obtained in different ways, e.g., by manual configuration, or through ILMI interaction with the neighbor system.

cesmChanCnfGrpTable.name: cesmChanCnfGrpTable
cesmChanCnfGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical channel interface there are 4 entries for 4 DS1s in case of CESM-4P in case of CESM-8P it can have 263 entries. For CESM-T3/E3 , this will have only one entry.

cesCnfChanNum.name: cesCnfChanNum
cesCnfChanNum.description: Refers to the virtual connection no. In case of CESM-4P the range is 16..19 (only for 4 entries). for CESM-8t1 we can have 192 and for CESM-8e1 we can have 248 channels. For CESM-T3/E3 we can have only one connection. For CESM-T1/E1/T3/E3, channel number starts from 35 in Release2.2

cesChanRowStatus.name: cesChanRowStatus
cesChanRowStatus.description: This indicates the channel status 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY 4 ==> Setting this object to outOfService takes the channel out of service or brings the channel 'down'. The channel can be brought 'up' again by setting the object to mod.

cesMapPortNum.name: cesMapPortNum
cesMapPortNum.description: In case of CESM-4P this variable specifies the port number to which this channel is associated. Mappings are as - Port 1 - channel 16, 2-17, 3-18, 4-19 (it can take value from 1..4) In CESM-8 this variable gives mapping between logical channel and physical line number. In case of CESM-8P instead of this cesChanPortNum will be used to have the mapping between Channel and logical Port. In case of CESM-T3 it can be 1..1

cesMapVpi.name: cesMapVpi
cesMapVpi.description: The value of this object is equal to the VPI used for the emulated circuit represented by this connection. In MGX8220( formerly AXIS) Implementaion slot number of the card will be used for this.

cesMapVci.name: cesMapVci
cesMapVci.description: This specifies VCI for emulated circuit represented by this VC. Our Implementation cesCnfChanNum will be used for this. In case of CESM-4P valid range is 16..19. In case of CESM-8P valid range is 32..279. In case of CESM-T3/E3 valid value is 32.

cesCBRService.name: cesCBRService
cesCBRService.description: This specifies data type supported by the CBR service Only Unstructured mode is supported in CESM-4P CESM-8P supports both structured and unstructured mode for T1/E1 and supports only unstructured mode in case of T3/E3. In CESM-T3 only unstructured is supported.

cesCBRClockMode.name: cesCBRClockMode
cesCBRClockMode.description: This specifies clocking mode of the CBR service Only synchronous mode is supported in CESM-4P Structured mode is always synchronous. CESM -T3 will support only synchronous.

cesCas.name: cesCas
cesCas.description: Specifies if CAS bits are carried by the service. This also selects which AAL1 format should be used. Only basic mode is supported for unstructured connections Only basic mode is supported in CESM-4P and CESM-T3E3 . If type is ccs then this particular VC is carrying Signaling information. ccs option is not supported in CESM-8T1E1. In CESM-8T1/E1 all channels on a line should have the same value. basicNoPointer should be used for adding 1x64 basic connections without an AAL1 pointer ( CES-IS 2.0 compliance ). when cesCas = basic, for 1x64 connections, cells will be generated with a AAL1 pointer.Similarly while receiving, pointer will be expected in the incoming cells. ds1SfCasMF and ds1EsfCasMF should be used when line level multiframe sync to be enabled.

cesPartialFill.name: cesPartialFill
cesPartialFill.description: Specifies the number of user octets per cell, if partial cell fill is used. 47 means partial fill disabled. Partial fill is not supported in CESM-4P Ranges for partial fill are: T1 struct 25 - 47 T1 unstruct 33 - 47 E1 struct 20 - 47 E1 unstruct 33 - 47 and partial fill for any channel should always exceed the number of time slots assigned to that channel.

cesBufMaxSize.name: cesBufMaxSize
cesBufMaxSize.description: Specifies the maximum size in octets of egress buffer. CESM - 4P: Should be at least 0.6*CDVRxT for a T1 line and 0.7 * CDVRxT for a E1 line. 0 can be specified to internally compute the value Defaults for CESM-8T1E1 and CESM-T3E3 ------------------------------------- Default value of cesBufMaxSize is 0. Maximum value for CESM-8T1E1 and CESM-T3E3 ------------------------------------------- For T1 UDT and E1 UDT : 16224 bytes For T1 SDT : 384 * N bytes For E1 SDT : 417 * N bytes For T3 UDT and E3 UDT : 16224 bytes where N is the number of timeslots assigned in Nx64 connection. For T1-UDT and E1 UDT use N = 32 . Minimum value for CESM-8T1E1 and CESM-T3E3 ------------------------------------------- In CESM-8T1/E1 and CESM-T3E3 this object ( unit in bytes ) should be at least the greater of (1) CDVT in frames * 2 * N (2) ( CDVT in frames + number of frames in two cells ) * N where N is the number of timeslots assigned in Nx64 connection. For T1-UDT and E1-UDT use N = 32.

cesCDVRxT.name: cesCDVRxT
cesCDVRxT.description: Specifies maximum cell arrival jitter that the reassembly process will tolerate. In case of CESM-8P it should be in increment of 125 micro secs and Max limit are as follows. T1 = 24 ms E1 = 26 ms T3 = 1.447 ms and E3 = 1.884 ms. Default values in CESM-8T1/E1 and CESM-T3/E3.: For T1 and E1 , 1000 microsecs. For T3 and E3 , 1000 microsecs.

cesCellLossIntegrationPeriod.name: cesCellLossIntegrationPeriod
cesCellLossIntegrationPeriod.description: Specifies the cell loss integration period in milliseconds

cesChanLocRmtLpbkState.name: cesChanLocRmtLpbkState
cesChanLocRmtLpbkState.description: Loopback on cellbus in egress direction.

cesChanTestType.name: cesChanTestType
cesChanTestType.description: This is the type of the test 1 = Test Continuity 2 = Test Delay 3 = no test is initated 4 = test continuity with sti cell format 5 = test delay with sti cell format

cesChanTestState.name: cesChanTestState
cesChanTestState.description: This shows the state of the test 1 = Passed 2 = Failed 3 = In Progress 4 = Not In Progress

cesChanRTDResult.name: cesChanRTDResult
cesChanRTDResult.description: This is round trip delay in milliseconds

cesChanPortNum.name: cesChanPortNum
cesChanPortNum.description: This indicates to which logical port this connection belongs. Applicable on CESM-8T1/E1 or CESM-T3/E3. 1.. 248 for E1 1.. 192 for T1 1.. 1 for T3 Only applicable to CESM-8P

cesChanConnType.name: cesChanConnType
cesChanConnType.description: This indicates the type of connection. 1 = PVC 2 = SVC 3 ==> SPVC connection Only applicable to CESM-8P and CESM-T3/E3.

cesChanStrauSciNum.name: cesChanStrauSciNum
cesChanStrauSciNum.description: This indicates the type of connection. 1 = Normal Channel (nonStrauChannel(0) ) 2 = SCI 1 i.e bit 1 & 2 3 = SCI 2 i.e bit 3 & 4 4 = SCI 3 i.e bit 5 & 6 5 = SCI 4 i.e bit 7 & 8 Currently not supported in CESM-8 Not applicable for CESM-4 and CESM-T3/E3

cesChanIdleDetEnable.name: cesChanIdleDetEnable
cesChanIdleDetEnable.description: This indicates the type of Idle detection enabled 1 = Idle code detection is disabled. 2 = This will enable Idle detection whenver it detects Onhook in ABCD bits. Onhook code is configurable using cesChanOnhookCode. Applicable in structured mode. 3 = This will enable payload Idle code detection. Idle pattern is configurable through cesChanIdleSignalCode variable. Only applicable to CESM-8T1/E1 and non strau channels This will be supported in future release

cesChanIdleSignalCode.name: cesChanIdleSignalCode
cesChanIdleSignalCode.description: When cesChanIdleDetEnable = enableIdlePatternDet 3. This object will carry value 0..0xff and this will indicate Idle pattern in DS0 time slots. Only applicable to CESM-8P and not supported in this release.

cesChanIdleCodeIntgnPeriod.name: cesChanIdleCodeIntgnPeriod
cesChanIdleCodeIntgnPeriod.description: This variable indicates the Integration period in seconds whenever cesChanIdleDetEnable = enableIdlePatternDet Only applicable to CESM-8P and not supported in this release.

cesChanOnhookCode.name: cesChanOnhookCode
cesChanOnhookCode.description: When cesChanIdleDetEnable = enableOnhookDet 1. This will carry value 0..3 for framing mode SF. 2. This will carry value 0..15 for framing mode ESF/e1Cas. Only applicable for CESM-8T1/E1

cesChanConditionedData.name: cesChanConditionedData
cesChanConditionedData.description: This byte will indicate Idle data to be sent towards the line whenever channels goes in to Underrun Only applicable for CESM-8T1/E1

cesmChanExtTrgIdleSupp.name: cesmChanExtTrgIdleSupp
cesmChanExtTrgIdleSupp.description: Using this variable we can initiate Idle suppression on the connection. This can be set by external signalling device. Only applicable to CESM-8T1/E1.

cesmChanConditionedSigCode.name: cesmChanConditionedSigCode
cesmChanConditionedSigCode.description: This byte will indicate Signal code to be sent sent towards the line whenever channels goes in to Underrun Only applicable to CESM-8T1/E1

cesLocalVpi.name: cesLocalVpi
cesLocalVpi.description: This VPI together with the local VCI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection, this object is read only, therefore it'll be assigned by SM to 0.

cesLocalVci.name: cesLocalVci
cesLocalVci.description: This VCI together with the local VPI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection, this object is read only, therefore it'll be assigned by SM to 0.

cesLocalNSAP.name: cesLocalNSAP
cesLocalNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL

cesRemoteVpi.name: cesRemoteVpi
cesRemoteVpi.description: This VPI together with the remote VCI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection. The value should be 0 for a DACS connection in MGX

cesRemoteVci.name: cesRemoteVci
cesRemoteVci.description: This VCI together with the remote VPI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection. The value should be 0 for a DACS connection in MGX

cesRemoteNSAP.name: cesRemoteNSAP
cesRemoteNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL

cesMastership.name: cesMastership
cesMastership.description: This is used by PXM to determine if this end point is master or slave, a new type unknown is added to identify the SM in MGX8220(formerly AXIS) shelf and the SM in MGX shelf. In MGX8220 shelf, user can still use addchan to add a channel without specifying X/Y/P parameters. But in MGX shelf, if the user uses addchan without X/Y/P set (based on this object being set to type 3 unknown), SPM on PXM will reject the request. It must be supplied in connection setup request

cesVpcFlag.name: cesVpcFlag
cesVpcFlag.description: This represents the connection type, used for PXM to identify VPC/VCC but CESM card doesn't use it always set to vcc for CESM card

cesConnServiceType.name: cesConnServiceType
cesConnServiceType.description: This specifies the service type 1 ==> Constant Bit Rate 2 ==> Variable Bit Rate 3 ==> Not used 4 ==> Unspecified Bit Rate 5 ==> ATM frame relay 6 ==> standard ABR 7 ==> foresight ABR Note that this is used by PXM card, SV+ doesn't need to set it, if not set in the connection setup request, it'll be defaulted to CBR type for CESM. Also to make it compatible with existing AUSM MIB definition, value 3 is not used. The following types are being added for PNNI support and are based on UNI 4.0. cbr1 (21) - CBR.1 vbr1rt (22) - Real time VBR.1 vbr2rt (23) - Real time VBR.2 vbr3rt (24) - Real time VBR.3 vbr1nrt(25) - Non Real time VBR.1 vbr2nrt(26) - Non Real time VBR.2 vbr3nrt(27) - Non Real time VBR.3 ubr1 (28) - UBR.1 ubr2 (29) - UBR.2 stdabr (30) - TM 4.0 compliant standard ABR cbr2 (31) - CBR.2 cbr3 (32) - CBR.3 Note that for CESM, the only valid connection type for PNNI support is cbr1(21). Other enumerations have been added for the sake of consistency across Narrow-Band service modules.

cesRoutingPriority.name: cesRoutingPriority
cesRoutingPriority.description: This is used by PXM to determine how important this connection is when selecting connections to route

cesMaxCost.name: cesMaxCost
cesMaxCost.description: Maximum allowed cost. It is related to Cost Based Routing. This is used by PXM so that it won't choose a path with a cost greater than this configured level. This is not necessary to be provided in the connection setup request, if not provided, the default value 255 will be used. When used with PAR controller the valid range is 1..65535 and the default value is 255. When used with PNNI controller the valid range is 1..2147483647 and the default value is 2147483647.

cesRestrictTrunkType.name: cesRestrictTrunkType
cesRestrictTrunkType.description: Restricted trunk type for routing, used by PXM. It specifies that the connection either cannot be routed over satelite trunks, or terrestrial trunks, or it can be on any type of trunk. It is not necessary to be provide in the connection setup request, the default value is noresriction(1).

cesConnPCR.name: cesConnPCR
cesConnPCR.description: Peak cell rate,if not provided in the connection setup request,it will be computed as follows, For CESM-8T1/E1 - N * 64 Kbps , where N = Number of timeslots assigned to this channel. For CESM-T3, the value is 44736 Kbps For CESM-E3, the value is 34368 Kbps.

cesConnMCR.name: cesConnMCR
cesConnMCR.description: Minimum cell rate,if not provided in the connection setup request,it will be computed as follows, For CESM-8T1/E1 - N * 64 Kbps , where N = Number of timeslots assigned to this channel. For CESM-T3, the value is 44736 Kbps For CESM-E3, the value is 34368 Kbps.

cesConnPercentUtil.name: cesConnPercentUtil
cesConnPercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by theis end-point. For CESM-8T1/E1/T3/E3 , the value is 100%

cesmConnRemotePCR.name: cesmConnRemotePCR
cesmConnRemotePCR.description: Peak cell rate of the other end, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

cesmConnRemoteMCR.name: cesmConnRemoteMCR
cesmConnRemoteMCR.description: Minimum cell rate of the other end, if not set in MGX, will be derived from the end point parameter

cesmConnRemotePercentUtil.name: cesmConnRemotePercentUtil
cesmConnRemotePercentUtil.description: This is the expected long-term utilization of the channel by the other end-point.

cesmConnForeSightEnable.name: cesmConnForeSightEnable
cesmConnForeSightEnable.description: This object is used by the controller(PAR/PNNI/TAG) to set up the Qbin for the connection. This is notapplicable to CESM-8T1/E1/T3/E3.

cesmConnFGCRAEnable.name: cesmConnFGCRAEnable
cesmConnFGCRAEnable.description: enables/disables Frame based GCRA (early packet discard). This is not applicable to CESM-8T1/E1/T3/E3.

cesmChanReroute.name: cesmChanReroute
cesmChanReroute.description: This is used by the administrator to trigger the re-routing of the connection. The rerouting takes effect, when this object is set to true(1). When set to false (2), no action is taken. A get on this object always returns false (2). This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

cesmConnAdminStatus.name: cesmConnAdminStatus
cesmConnAdminStatus.description: This object specifies channel admin status. This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

cesmChanNumNextAvailable.name: cesmChanNumNextAvailable
cesmChanNumNextAvailable.description: This variable contains the next unused channel number of the possible 248. This number can be used in channel config table. cesChanNumNextAvailable gets updated whenever this number is used to create a new logical channel. Value 0 for this variable indicates that no more channels are available. In CESM 8-port card), the maximum number of values for this variable is 248 (i.e. 32 ..279). Only applicable to CESM-8T1/E1/T3/E3.

cesmChanCntGrpTable.name: cesmChanCntGrpTable
cesmChanCntGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical channel interface there are 4 entries for 4 DS1s in case of CESM-4P In case of CESM-8P it can have 352 entries.

cesCntChanNum.name: cesCntChanNum
cesCntChanNum.description: Refers to the channel Number 16 - 19 for CESM-4P 32 - 279 for CESM-8t1e1 32 for CESM-T3/E3

cesChanState.name: cesChanState
cesChanState.description: This variable indicates the connection status failed(4) is added to distinguish between alarm (when the connection segment is not actually broken) and failed(when the segment is actually broken). This is applicable only to the PNNI environment.

cesXmtATMState.name: cesXmtATMState
cesXmtATMState.description: This variable indicates the transmit state of channel on the ATM side (towards the network).

cesRcvATMState.name: cesRcvATMState
cesRcvATMState.description: This variable indicates the receive state of channel on the ATM side (from the network).

cesCellLossStatus.name: cesCellLossStatus
cesCellLossStatus.description: When cells are lost for the CellLossIntegrationPeriod the value is set to loss ( 2). when cells are no longer lost, the value is set to noLoss(1).

cesReassCells.name: cesReassCells
cesReassCells.description: The number of cells played out to T1/E1/T3E3 interface. It excludes cells that were discarded for any reason.

cesGenCells.name: cesGenCells
cesGenCells.description: The number of cells generated from T1/E1/T3E3 interface and sent towards network.

cesHdrErrors.name: cesHdrErrors
cesHdrErrors.description: The number of AAL-1 header errors detected and possibly corrected. Header errors include correctable and uncor- rectable CRC, plus bad parity.

cesPointerReframes.name: cesPointerReframes
cesPointerReframes.description: The number of events in which the AAL1 reassembler found that an SDT pointer is not where it is expected and the and the pointer must be reacquired. Not supported in cesm8P due limitation in AAL1 SAR. Not applicable for CESM-4T1/E1 and CESM-T3/E3

cesLostCells.name: cesLostCells
cesLostCells.description: The number of cells lost in egress direction due to AAL 1 header errors and missing cells.

cesBufUnderflows.name: cesBufUnderflows
cesBufUnderflows.description: The number of buffer underflows in Egress direction Not supported in cesm8P due limitation in AAL1 SAR.

cesBufOverflows.name: cesBufOverflows
cesBufOverflows.description: The number of buffer overflows in Egress direction Not supported in cesm8P due limitation in AAL1 SAR.

cesIngrDiscardedBytes.name: cesIngrDiscardedBytes
cesIngrDiscardedBytes.description: The number of bytes discarded due to shelf alarm in ingress direction from port data. Not supported in CESM-8P.

cesUflowInsCells.name: cesUflowInsCells
cesUflowInsCells.description: The Number of All 1's cells inserted in case of Egress Buffer Underflow Not supported in CESM-8P.

cesOflowDropBytes.name: cesOflowDropBytes
cesOflowDropBytes.description: The Number of bytes discarded in Egress direction because of Egress buffer overflow Not supported in CESM-8P.

cesCellSeqMismatchCnt.name: cesCellSeqMismatchCnt
cesCellSeqMismatchCnt.description: The Number of times SAR received a valid out of sequence AAL-1 cell from CellBus.

counterClrButton.name: counterClrButton
counterClrButton.description: writing a value of 2 resets all the counters

cesChanSecUptime.name: cesChanSecUptime
cesChanSecUptime.description: The Number of seconds channel is in service only applicable for CESM-8P

cesChanSignalingStatus.name: cesChanSignalingStatus
cesChanSignalingStatus.description: This variable indicates the connection signalling status Connection will be in Idle suppression mode if it in on-hook. Not applicable for T3E3 and CESM-4P.

cesChanStatusBitMap.name: cesChanStatusBitMap
cesChanStatusBitMap.description: This variable indicates the consolidated bit map of the channel alarm state. Individual bit positions are as defined below. Bit position Fail/Alarm Reason ------------ ---------- ------ 0 Alarm Reserved 1 Alarm n/w side AIS/RDI Rx 2 Fail Conditioned(A bit from n/w) 3 Alarm Reserved 4 Fail Reserved 5 Fail Reserved 6 Alarm Reserved 7 Alarm Cell loss alarm Fail bitmap mask : 0x34 Alarm bitmap mask: 0xCB This object is not applicable to MGX Release 1.x.

cesmPortCnfGrpTable.name: cesmPortCnfGrpTable
cesmPortCnfGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical port interface there are 192 entries for 8 DS1s or 248 entries for 8 E1s

cesPortNum.name: cesPortNum
cesPortNum.description: This is logical port number. If we have T1 card then the maximum port number is 192 and if we have E1 card the maximum port number can be 248 for T3 only one port is supported.

cesPortRowStatus.name: cesPortRowStatus
cesPortRowStatus.description: This variable enables or modifies the port 1- add 2 - del 3 - mod

cesPortLineNum.name: cesPortLineNum
cesPortLineNum.description: This represents the line number to which this port is associated. For T3 only one line is supported.

cesPortType.name: cesPortType
cesPortType.description: This represents port type whether it is carrying subrate circuits strau. If it is strau port then it can have only one DS0 time slot. In case of unstructured all the time slots will be allocated to that. Strau ports are not supported in CESM-8T1/E1 or CESM-T3E3. framingOnVcDisconnect is similar to unstructured port during normal operation. In case of channel failure, line data will be looped back towards line. CESM-T3E3 card will support only unstructured mode.

cesPortDs0ConfigBitMap.name: cesPortDs0ConfigBitMap
cesPortDs0ConfigBitMap.description: This respesents bit map of DS0s for a line which are used to form this logical port. Bit 0 represents DS0-1.

cesPortNumOfDs0Slot.name: cesPortNumOfDs0Slot
cesPortNumOfDs0Slot.description: This represents number of DS0 time slots configured to this Port. If the port type is strau then this can not have more than 1 DS0 time slot.

cesPortNumOfSCIPerDS0.name: cesPortNumOfSCIPerDS0
cesPortNumOfSCIPerDS0.description: This is applicable only to the Strau Port. represents number of subcircuit in the DS0 time slot. 8 = there are 8 no .of 8kbps links (1 bit) 4 = there are 4 no .of 16kbps links (2 bit) 2 = there are 2 no .of 32kbps links (4 bit) Currently not supported in CESM-8

cesPortSpeed.name: cesPortSpeed
cesPortSpeed.description: Configured speed of port in kbps Max speed for T1 = 1544 Max speed for E1 = 2038 Max speed for T3 = 44736 Max spped for E3 = 34368

cesPortState.name: cesPortState
cesPortState.description: This variable indicates the state of the logical port

cesPortBERTEnable.name: cesPortBERTEnable
cesPortBERTEnable.description: This variable enables BERT This object is not supported in CESM-T3E3.

cesPortNextAvailable.name: cesPortNextAvailable
cesPortNextAvailable.description: This variable contains the next UNUSED logical port number of the possible 32 DS0s * n ports. This number can be used in channel config table, the cesportNextAvailable gets updated if the number gets used to create a logical port. A '0' indicates that no more ports are available.

cesPortsUsedLine1.name: cesPortsUsedLine1
cesPortsUsedLine1.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 1

cesPortsUsedLine2.name: cesPortsUsedLine2
cesPortsUsedLine2.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 2

cesPortsUsedLine3.name: cesPortsUsedLine3
cesPortsUsedLine3.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 3

cesPortsUsedLine4.name: cesPortsUsedLine4
cesPortsUsedLine4.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 4

cesPortsUsedLine5.name: cesPortsUsedLine5
cesPortsUsedLine5.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 5

cesPortsUsedLine6.name: cesPortsUsedLine6
cesPortsUsedLine6.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 6

cesPortsUsedLine7.name: cesPortsUsedLine7
cesPortsUsedLine7.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 7

cesPortsUsedLine8.name: cesPortsUsedLine8
cesPortsUsedLine8.description: Each bits set represents a DS0 that is used by all the logical ports defined so far for that DS1, the most significant byte is invalid for DS1 This is for line 8

cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.name: cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable
cesmPortCnfResPartGrpTable.description: This table contains the configuration of port resource partition This is applicable for MGX8820(formerly AXIS) Rel. 5 and MGX.

cesmResPartPortNum.name: cesmResPartPortNum
cesmResPartPortNum.description: This is the logical port number, the index to this table. If we have T1 card then the maximum port number is 192 and if we have E1 card the maximum port number can be 248. CESM-T3/E3 supports only one port.

cesmResPartCtrlrNum.name: cesmResPartCtrlrNum
cesmResPartCtrlrNum.description: This is index for controller using the port

cesmResPartRowStatus.name: cesmResPartRowStatus
cesmResPartRowStatus.description: This will add, delete or modify the partition. 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY

cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail.name: cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail
cesmResPartNumOfLcnAvail.description: This represents number of LCNs available for this controller and this port. In CESM-T3/E3 and 8-T1/E1,this value is 1.

cesmResPartLcnLow.name: cesmResPartLcnLow
cesmResPartLcnLow.description: This represents low end of reserved LCN In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, this refers to the logical port.

cesmResPartLcnHigh.name: cesmResPartLcnHigh
cesmResPartLcnHigh.description: This represents high end of reserved LCN In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, this refers to the logical port.

cesmResPartIngrPctBW.name: cesmResPartIngrPctBW
cesmResPartIngrPctBW.description: The percentage of total ingress bandwidth reserved. In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, as there is only one LCN per port and it could be used by only one controller,this value is 100% for that controller.

cesmResPartEgrPctBW.name: cesmResPartEgrPctBW
cesmResPartEgrPctBW.description: The percentage of total egress bandwidth reserved In CESM-8T1/E1 and T3/E3, as there is only one LCN per port and it could be used by only one controller,this value is 100% for that controller.

cesmResPartCtrlrID.name: cesmResPartCtrlrID
cesmResPartCtrlrID.description: This is the controller identifier for the resource patition. The default value is set for PNNI controller.

cesmEndPtMapGrpTable.name: cesmEndPtMapGrpTable
cesmEndPtMapGrpTable.description: There are 248 entries and port num will uniquely identify a row. For CESM-8T1/E1 , only 248 ports are possible. For CESM-T3/E3, only one port is possible.

cesEndPortNum.name: cesEndPortNum
cesEndPortNum.description: Refers to the logical port index CESM-8E1 supports 248 ports. CESM-8T1 supports 192 ports. CESM-T3/E3 supports only one port.

cesEndChanNum.name: cesEndChanNum
cesEndChanNum.description: Logical connection number for above cesEndPortNum

cesEndLineNum.name: cesEndLineNum
cesEndLineNum.description: Refers to the physical line index In case T3 only one line will be supported.

frChanCnfGrpTable.name: frChanCnfGrpTable
frChanCnfGrpTable.description: The config table is for logical channel interface (upto 4000 entries). The actual number of entries supported by a card depends on the type of card. eg: FRSM-4T1/E1 supports 256 entries FRSM-8T1/E1 supports 1000 entries FRSM-T3/E3/HS2/HS2B-HSSI/T3B/E3B supports 2000 entries FRSM-2CT3/HS2B-12IN1 supports 4000 entries FRSM12 supports 16000 entries

chanNum.name: chanNum
chanNum.description: Refers to the virtual connection index Note that the actual range of the index supported by a card depends on the type of card. eg: FRSM-4T1/E1 supports a range from 16..271 (256 entries) FRSM-8T1/E1 supports a range from 16..1015 (1000 entries) FRSM-T3/E3/HS2/HS2B-HSSI/T3B/E3B supports a range from 16..2015 (2000 entries) FRSM-2CT3/HS2B-12IN1 supports a range from 16..4015 (4000 entries) For FRSM12 Card: Byte 3 = Chassis Number, Byte 2 = Slot Number, Byte 1 & 0 = channel Number. Lower two bytes range from 16..16015 (16000 entries)

chanRowStatus.name: chanRowStatus
chanRowStatus.description: This will add, delete or modify the channel 1 ==> ADD 2 ==> DELETE 3 ==> MODIFY Setting this object to outOfService takes the channel out of service or brings the channel 'down'. The channel can be brought 'up' again by setting the object to mod

chanPortNum.name: chanPortNum
chanPortNum.description: Refers to the logical ports that are possible on this card, the user must set this variable For FRSM12 Card: This object contains the port's ifIndex value.

dLCI.name: dLCI
dLCI.description: This variable is the DLCI number of the channel. The user has to set this variable. All the connections on the same port should have a unique DLCI number. Note that if we are adding a channel to a port that has LMI signalling enabled, then we can not use DLCI number 0(ANNEX A & D) and 1023(STRATA LMI). For FRSM12 Card: For FR header length of 2-bytes, DLCI range is (0 .. 1023) and 0, 1007, 1023 DLCIs cannot be used. For FR header length of 4-bytes, DLCI range is (0 .. 8388607) and 0, 8257535 DLCIs cannot be used.

egressQSelect.name: egressQSelect
egressQSelect.description: Selects one out of two possible port queues. The default port queue number is 1 which is the high pririty queue. 1 = High priority queue 2 = Low priority queue 3 = Indicates that this entry is not used (eg: in FRSM-VHS, chanServType indicates the channel service type and would determine the queue to which the channel gets mapped) For FRSM12 Card: This object is used to select between the two ATM-COS queues in the egress direction.

ingressQDepth.name: ingressQDepth
ingressQDepth.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before it starts dropping the cells. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (4510..'ffff'h). ingressQDepth should be greater than ingressQECNThresh and ingressQDEThresh For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

ingressQECNThresh.name: ingressQECNThresh
ingressQECNThresh.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before it starts flow control. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (0..'ffff'h). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

ingressQDEThresh.name: ingressQDEThresh
ingressQDEThresh.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before they become discard eligible. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (0..'ffff'h). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

egressQDepth.name: egressQDepth
egressQDepth.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before it starts dropping the cells. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (0..'ffff'h). egressQDepth should be greater than egressQDEThresh and egressQECNThresh For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

egressQDEThresh.name: egressQDEThresh
egressQDEThresh.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before they become discard eligible. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (0..'ffff'h). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

egressQECNThresh.name: egressQECNThresh
egressQECNThresh.description: This variable sets the max depth for queue, before it starts flow control. It is defined in terms of number of bytes. In all cards except the FRSM-VHS card, the range is limited to (0..'ffff'h). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

deTaggingEnable.name: deTaggingEnable
deTaggingEnable.description: The default value is 2. This variable enables DE tagging in the ingress direction only. enable = 1 disable = 2 For FRSM12 Card: When this object is disabled, the ingress policer will never set the DE bit to 1 in the Frame Relay frames even if the incoming frame exceeds the Bc bucket.

cir.name: cir
cir.description: The default value is 2400 cir defines committed information rate cir is in bits per second Maximum value for cir for an E1 card is 2048000 and for a T1 card is 1536000. cir has to be less than or equal to the port speed. Maximum value for cir for an E3 card is 34368000, for a T3 card is 44736000m, and for HSSI it is 52000000. Note that for FRSM-2CT3 card, the peak value of permissible CIR is 1536000. Maximum value for FRSM-HS2B-12IN1 is 10240000 Any value from 1 to 2399 will be rounded off to 2400. For FRSM12 Card: The range is 0-44736000 bps for T3, and The range is 0-34368000 bps for E3. cir can be 0 only for chanServType of uBR.

bc.name: bc
bc.description: The default value is 5100 bc defines burst committed. bc is in bytes. bc can not be 0 when cir is not 0. bc has to be 0 if cir is 0. The peak value for bc in FRSM-VHS cards is (2^21 -1), i.e. 2097151 and for all other cards, it is 65535. For FRSM-VHS cards, the relation between CIR and Bc should be such that Tc is always less than 512 seconds. For FRSM12 Card: The range is 0-2097151

be.name: be
be.description: The default value is 5100 be defines the burst excess. be can not be 0 when cir is 0. be is in bytes. The peak value for be in FRSM-VHS cards is (2^21 -1), i.e. 2097151 and for all other cards, it is 65535. For FRSM-VHS cards, setting the value of 2091751 will cause the policing to be disabled. For FRSM12 Card: The range is 0-2097151

ibs.name: ibs
ibs.description: The default value is 100 ibs should be less or equal to bc when cir is greater than 0. ibs has to be 0 when cir is 0. The peak value for ibs in FRSM-VHS cards is (2^21 -1), i.e. 2097151 and for all other cards, it is 65535. For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

foreSightEnable.name: foreSightEnable
foreSightEnable.description: The default value is 2 This variable sets foreSight option Note that when you enable foresight option then you can modify qir, mir and pir, otherwise you CAN NOT change these values if you are disabling foresight or if foresight option is already disabled. The RATE CONTROL FEATURE has to be ON in order to enable foresight and also modify its parameter. enable = 1 disable = 2 For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

qir.name: qir
qir.description: The dafault is 160 qir is defined in fastpackets/sec and it defines quiescent information rate for Foresight. 1 cell/sec is equal to 16 fastpackets/sec. Following information about cps is for reference only: The peak value for qir in FRSM-VHS cards is 285714 cps and for all other cards, it is 10000 cps. For FRSM-VHS cards, cell will be the ATM cell (48 byte payload). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

mir.name: mir
mir.description: The dafault is 160 mir is defined in fastpackets/sec and it defines minimum information rate for Foresight. 1 cell/sec is equal to 16 fastpackets/sec. Following information about cps is for reference only: The peak value for qir in FRSM-VHS cards is 285714 cps and for all other cards, it is 10000 cps. For FRSM-VHS cards, cell will be the ATM cell (48 byte payload). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

pir.name: pir
pir.description: The dafault is 160 pir is defined in fastpackets/sec and it defines peak information rate for Foresight. 1 cell/sec is equal to 16 fastpackets/sec. Following information about cps is for reference only: The peak value for qir in FRSM-VHS cards is 285714 cps and for all other cards, it is 10000 cps. For FRSM-VHS cards, cell will be the ATM cell (48 byte payload). For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

chanLocRmtLpbkState.name: chanLocRmtLpbkState
chanLocRmtLpbkState.description: The default is disable. This variable enables or disables the remote loopback for each channel. When you enable this option on a connection (channel) then all the cells that are coming from the network side would be looped back toward the network and all the frames coming from the user side would be dropped. This channel remote loopback has nothing to do with the chanTestType option, each one does a different function. For example, the channel remote loopback is used for looping the data toward the network and if this connection is terminated on an IPX then they can put a test equipment and measure some of the characteristics of the network. 1 = enable 2 = disable For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

chanTestType.name: chanTestType
chanTestType.description: The default is notest. The chanTestType starts testing the continuity or delay of a connection. It sends specific cell patterns toward the network and the terminating end of this connection has to be an AXIS or ASI of a BPX in order for this test to be working. The receiving node would loop back when it receives these cells. The test should be done in about couple of seconds. The testcon tests the continuity of the connection and testdelay uses the same test except that it measures for delay through the network. To test the delay follow this procedure: a- set chanTestType to testdelay b- read chanTestState till it is Pass or Fail c- Read chanRTDResult for the delay if it is Pass *Note that the chanTestType would go back to notest when the test is completed To test the continuity follow this procedure: a- set chanTestType to testcon b- read chanTestState till it is Pass or Fail *Note that the chanTestType would go back to notest when the test is completed You CAN NOT select 2 tests back to back, you have selcelt one and wait the result and then start the other one. SYNTAX When you select testdelay This is the type of the test 1 = Test Continuity 2 = Test Delay 3 = No Test

chanTestState.name: chanTestState
chanTestState.description: This shows the state of the test When you add a connection then the chanTestState becomes notinprogress and when you select any test, it would go to inprogress state and after it completes the test, it will go to failed or passed state. 1 = Passed 2 = Failed 3 = In Progress 4 = Not In Progress

chanRTDResult.name: chanRTDResult
chanRTDResult.description: This is round trip delay in milliseconds. When you select testdelay option for the chanTestType, the result of the test that is measured in milliseconds can be read in chanRTDResult.

chanType.name: chanType
chanType.description: sets channel type Type 1 is frame-relay network interworking (NIW-unicast) type 2 is service interworking with out any SDU translation type 3 is service interworking with SDU translation type 4 is frame-relay UNI, currently mode-1a which is ALL5 type 5 is frame forwarding types 1,2,3 and 5 are supported as explained above type 4 (frame-relay UNI) is NOT supported type 6 is also supported. It means frame-relay Network Interworking with DLCI in FRSSCS-PDU always set to 1022 For FRSM12 Card: frFUNI is not supported.

chanFECNconfig.name: chanFECNconfig
chanFECNconfig.description: sets FECN config mapEFCI valid only for SIW The FECN bits in frame-relay are mapped to EFCI bit in the ATM cells.

chanDEtoCLPmap.name: chanDEtoCLPmap
chanDEtoCLPmap.description: sets mapping of CLP bit The DE bit is mapped to CLP bit in ATM cell in Case 2 and 3, the DE bit is ignored and CLP bit is set to a constant value For FRSM12 Card: Should not be mapCLP for chanType of frForward.

chanCLPtoDEmap.name: chanCLPtoDEmap
chanCLPtoDEmap.description: sets mapping of DE bit 1,2,3 valid for SIW 1,4 valid for NIW The CLP bit is mapped to DE bit in frame-relay in the Case of 2 and 3, the CLP bit is ignored and DE bit is set to a constant value ignoreCLP ignores CLP bit and DE bit remains as received. For FRSM12 Card: Should be ignoreCLP for chanType of frForward. Should not be setDEzero/setDEone for chanType of frNIW and frNIWReplace. Should not be ignoreCLP for chanType of frSIW-transparent and frSIW-translate.

chanEgrSrvRate.name: chanEgrSrvRate
chanEgrSrvRate.description: The channel egress cir. Maximum value for chanEgrSrvRate for an E1 card is 2048000 and for a T1 card is 1536000. chanEgrSrvRate has to be less than or equal to the port speed. Maximum value for chanEgrSrvRate for an E3 card is 34368000, for a T3 card is 44736000m, and for HSSI it is 52000000. Note that for FRSM-2CT3 card, the peak value of permissible chanEgrSrvRate is 1536000. For FRSM12 Card: This object is used only for CAC and the range will be same as the range for cir object. The Maximum value is 44736000m.

chanOvrSubOvrRide.name: chanOvrSubOvrRide
chanOvrSubOvrRide.description: This MIB variable allows one to add a new connection on a port even if it is over subscribed. For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

chanFrConnType.name: chanFrConnType
chanFrConnType.description: channel connection type 1 for pvc 2 for svc 3 for spvc 4 par (only for trunk connection) 5 pnni (only for trunk connection) 6 tag (only for trunk connection) For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

frCDRNumber.name: frCDRNumber
frCDRNumber.description: This is the key to correlate cell/frame counts, start/end record. For FRSM12 Card: Not Supported

frLocalVpi.name: frLocalVpi
frLocalVpi.description: This VPI together with the local VCI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection, this object is read only, therefore it'll be assigned by SM to 0.

frLocalVci.name: frLocalVci
frLocalVci.description: This VCI together with the local VPI and NSAP represents the local end point in this connection, this object is read only, therefore it'll be assigned by SM to be equal to DLCI.

frLocalNSAP.name: frLocalNSAP
frLocalNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL For FRSM12 Card: This object will have the NSAP format as required by the PNNI controller

frRemoteVpi.name: frRemoteVpi
frRemoteVpi.description: This VPI together with the remote VCI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection

frRemoteVci.name: frRemoteVci
frRemoteVci.description: This VCI together with the remote VPI and NSAP represents the remote end point in this connection

frRemoteNSAP.name: frRemoteNSAP
frRemoteNSAP.description: This NSAP is 20 bytes binary, among these 20 bytes: 13 bytes as prefix, 2 bytes for Cisco ID, 1 byte rsvd, 3 bytes for logical interface: slot (1 byte) and port number (2 bytes), the last byte is for SEL

frMastership.name: frMastership
